title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes. Place chicken in 13 x 9 casserole dish. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in glass casserole. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Place bowl back in microwave for 9 minutes on High.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Add cream of tartar.
Mix in well.
Pour hot syrup over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed.
Add vanilla.
Beat for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture loses its shape and starts to lose its gloss.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Stir in first mixture thoroughly.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix with 1 egg and oil.
Save 1 cup mixture.
Press remaining in oblong pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape small amounts of dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with fork. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill thoroughly and enjoy with broccoli, carrots, radishes, cauliflower and chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, mushrooms, sliced onion and black pepper.
Heat together.
Lay breasts in casserole, skin side up.
Pour mixture over breasts and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with strips of bacon and sliced boned chicken breast spread over top.
Seal with foil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bayou seafood casserole
directions: Melt and put aside the cream cheese and butter.
Saute butter, onion, pepper, mushrooms, shrimp and celery.
Add to the first mixture; mix well, then add soup, garlic powder, Tabasco, pepper, crabmeat and rice.
Mix well; place in casserole and top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the crushed pineapple with juice. Put the cherry pie filling on top and sprinkle with the cake mix. Top with the nuts and coconut.
Cut pieces of butter onto the top of this.
Do not mix; just dump or spread.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together; put in ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until heated through, bubbly and slightly brown. Good with chips, pita bread triangles or vegetables.

title: hillbilly hamburger
directions: Mix ground beef and onion; brown, then drain the grease.
Then put kidney beans and let simmer for 25 minutes, then eat.

title: orange-cool whip salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add orange juice. Refrigerate for approximately 1 hour, until slightly set but still has liquidity.
Stir in cottage cheese, Cool Whip and sliced orange or mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender (about 15 minutes).
Add green pepper (cut in strips).
Cook 3 minutes more.
Drain well.
Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to it to make 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into pineapple juice.
Add vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until it boils.
Add carrots, green pepper and pineapple.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients (except pecans) and mix well. Shape into ball and refrigerate, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Prepare fudge according to package directions.
Stir in pecans, raisins and marshmallows.
Spray a glass dish with Pam.
Place fudge in dish and refrigerate for 4 hours.
Very rich.
Serve small pieces!

title: crispix candy or "puppy chow"
directions: Melt first 3 items in the microwave until creamy.
Pour over Crispix cereal and mix carefully.
Put in paper bag with powdered sugar and shake to coat.
Dump mixture out on cookie sheet to cool.

title: 1-2-3 oriental pepper steak
directions: In bowl combine beef, soy sauce, 1/2 of your garlic, 3/4 teaspoon ginger and 1/2 cup beef broth.
Let stand 1 hour.
In skillet heat oil, remaining garlic and ginger.
Add peppers and onions, cook and stir 2 minutes until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat to low and stir in chicken broth and black pepper.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove vegetables from broth and place in bowl.
Bring broth mixture to boil over high heat; add beef; cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly until beef is cooked through. Return vegetables to pan with beef.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve with a rice side dish and stir-fry vegetables.

title: homemade potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients for dressing, mix well, and set aside.

title: bacon chestnut surprise
directions: Drain water chestnuts.
Cut strips of bacon long enough to wrap around chestnuts.
Spear with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Meanwhile, in a small pan, bring to a boil the catsup, sugar and mustard.
When bacon and chestnuts are finished, dip in syrup mixture.

title: ginny richards mother's rice pudding
directions: Scald one quart milk.
Add one orange peel spiral, lightly rinsed rice, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook 45 minutes; cover part of time.
Remove orange peel and add 1 cup light cream and 2 egg yolks and cook 20 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook until pudding sets.
Can be served warm or chilled. Top with fruit or raisins.
Serves 4 to 5 people.
Can be made several days ahead.

title: orange jelly
directions: Pour juice into 6 or 8-quart saucepan; stir in 2 1/2 cups water.
Measure sugar and set aside.
Stir Sure-Jell into juice; bring to a full boil over high heat.
Stir constantly.
At once stir in sugar.
Stir and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam in large metal spoon.
Immediately pour in hot glasses or jars.

title: carol's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, oil and shortening together.
Add eggs. Blend in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: comfort frosting
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cover and boil 3 minutes without stirring.
Uncover.
Do not stir and continue boiling until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread or reaches 242° on candy thermometer.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Put 1 layer on the bottom of punch bowl.
Spread 1/2 of crushed pineapple (and juice) on top of cake.
Slice 2 bananas and place on top of pineapple.
Next, add 1/2 of the strawberries (and juice).
Spread one box of prepared vanilla pudding on top of strawberries.
Repeat with second layer of cake, followed by pineapple, bananas, strawberries and pudding.
Spread on entire container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Decorate with cherries.

title: chocolate sour cream cookies
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored and thick.
Beat sugar in slowly; add melted chocolate.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda in alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla last. Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes, until just set.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello with hot water. Add ice cream and stir until mixed. Let cool until half jelled, then add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Mix the Knox unflavored gelatine and water in a small bowl and let sit for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix cranberry sauce, sugar and lemon juice; set aside.
At the end of 5 minutes, put the bowl with the gelatine mixture in hot water and stir until dissolved.
Stir the dissolved gelatine mixture into cranberry sauce.
Cover and put in fridge, until set, then fold in Cool Whip, and put into favorite mold.

title: javanese chicken
directions: Keep ingredients separated (amounts vary according to your preference).
Begin with noodles and just pile each ingredient on top.
Enjoy!

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and mayonnaise.
Beat well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk; heat to boiling, stirring.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables; set aside.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Add
top pie crust.
Cut slits in top.
Bake in a 435° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until crust is brown.

title: bunny becker's sugar angels
directions: Gather the ingredients and add and mix one at a time.
After the mixture is smooth and creamy, add 5 cups of flour gradually. When mixed well, cover and refrigerate.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Hollow out centers of tomatoes with grapefruit knife.
Chop all other ingredients with pieces of hollowed out tomatoes and stuff the tomatoes.
Let chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve on bibb lettuce.

title: quick icing
directions: Mix frosting and Cool Whip together.
Spread on cake.
You can add pineapple or coconut to alter taste.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water. When done (not too soft), cool and slice. Use very large pan. Mix ingredients and add to potatoes. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch greased pan, layer the ingredients as listed, cutting the margarine into pieces over the top of all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Blend with mixer. Combine ingredients and fill cupcake papers half full. Put a teaspoon of filling on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: best ever dinner rolls(recipe for bread machine)
directions: Measure ingredients into bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer.

Select dough or manual setting. When cycle is completed, remove the dough from the machine and either shape as desired or wrap in plastic wrap and place in refrigerator for up to 24 hours. If refrigerated, let set out for about 45 minutes to an hour before using. The easiest shape to make is to just divide the dough into equal parts and roll into balls in your hand. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Cover shaped dough with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place for 20 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated 400°F (205°C) oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Brush tops with butter or margarine. Makes about 20 to 24 rolls.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter over low heat. Add vanilla and salt. Mix and add chopped nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool until hardens.

title: doris' best ever gingersnaps
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices; stir lightly. Cut in shortening to resemble coarse crumbs.
Stir in molasses and egg.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind up all fruit.
Add sugar to fruit mixture and stir well; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in cup of water.
Add to fruit.
Add chopped nuts if desired.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: jiffy spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except spaghetti and cheese in 4 quart pressure pan. Cook 12 minutes at 15 lb. pressure. Reduce pressure quickly under cold running water. Serve over cooked spaghetti. Top with parmesan cheese.

title: oven stew
directions: Drain vegetables (fresh, frozen or canned).
Dump all in large casserole.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.
(Can go in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot toddy
directions: To every 10 pounds of grapes use 3 quarts water.
Let stand for 3 days.
Strain.
Add 5 pounds granulated sugar to juice.
Let stand 9 days or until fermentation ceases.
(Use stone jar covered with cloth.)
Bottle and cap tightly.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all
ingredients except chocolate chips and mix for 3 minutes.
Add
the	chips
and
mix
for another minute. Pour batter into a
prepared
Bundt
pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 55
to
minutes for Bundt pan or 40 to 45 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french cinnamon puffs
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Grease muffin cups (mini muffins work well).
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg, alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Immediately roll hot muffins in melted margarine and then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
A great recipe kis can help with!

title: meatballs
directions: Mix onion soup mix and water in saucepan; simmer 5 minutes. Pour 2 tablespoons of the tomato sauce into a cup; add garlic salt, thyme, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Mix well.
Add herb mixture to ground round and mix until blended.
Add remaining tomato sauce to onion soup mixture.

title: cheesie-herb dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a serving bowl, stirring until well mixed.
Serve with sesame seed crackers, any fresh and crisp cut vegetables such as carrots, celery, cucumber slices or with raw broccoli and/or cauliflower.

title: no egg cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand.
Mix remaining ingredients. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan or round pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain well.
Cut bacon in half.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Cut cabbage in half and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Fry cabbage in bacon fat until tender.
Add salt and pepper; stir in noodles and add bacon.

title: beet pickles
directions: Slice cooked beets and place in sterilized jars.
Heat ingredients and pour over beets.
Seal.
Excellent.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Heat oven at 325°.
With hands, combine cheese and sausage.
Add biscuit mix and blend thoroughly.
Roll into marble size balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 60 balls.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Brown meat in drippings. Remove meat and stir flour into dripping pan.
Brown lightly.
Add onions and cook 3 minutes.
Add beans, carrots, and meat.
Cover well with bouillon water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add herbs, celery, salt and pepper.
Cook until gravy is thick and dark. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat in heavy kettle.
Drain fat.
Put meat on rack.
Add 3/4 cup water, cover.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove meat, cut into 1/2 inch thick slices; return to kettle.
Bring to boil 3/4 cup water plus remaining ingredients except flour.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer until fork-tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if necessary.

title: chocolate shoo-fly pie
directions: Put all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Cut Crisco in with pastry blender until this resembles fine crumbs.

title: summer chicken
directions: Place chicken in microwave baking dish.
Tuck in garlic.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Squeeze juice from lemon over chicken pieces.
Top with rosemary sprigs.
Cover; microwave on Roast for 16 minutes.
Turn pieces and rotate dish. Cover; continue on a Medium setting for 12 minutes, or until tender and done.
Let stand.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan rolls(breakfast)
directions: Night before, partially defrost frozen bread dough and cut into 8 slices.
Lay each slice flat in bottom of a greased Bundt pan. Cover with butterscotch pudding, brown sugar, pecans, cinnamon and margarine.
Cover pan and let sit out overnight.
Do not refrigerate.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces and place in buttered 6 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine tomatoes, seasoning, sugar and cornstarch. Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Pour over bread; sprinkle with onion.
Decorate with cheese strips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use fresh tomatoes in season.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Beat soup, milk and eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Let set for 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Great dish for overnight guests!

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: Line pie pan.
Mix sugar, tapioca, cinnamon rhubarb and strawberries.
Pour
into
pastry
lined pan.
Dot with margarine. Cover
with top crust.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 40 minutes.
Crust will be nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits.

title: quick peppernuts
directions: Cream oleo and add sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg, syrup and anise oil.
Sift flour, soda and spices together and add to mixture.
Roll into thin rolls and cut with a sharp knife into 1/4-inch pieces.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown, approximately 6 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 1 1/2 cups water (without salt).
Cut in rather large pieces and mix with chicken and mushroom soups.
Add enough water to chicken broth to make 2 cups.
Then add to chicken and soup mixture.

title: orange tidbits
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar and pecans; mix well.
Stir in orange juice concentrate and butter.
Shape into individual bite-size balls; roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fry hamburger with onion; drain grease.
Add cabbage.
Add mixed vegetables, tomato paste and whole tomatoes (pour juice and all in).
Then add 2 cups water.
Let boil until done.
You may have to add more water while cooking.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Diagonally cut bread into 1 inch slices and place in baking dish.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, lightly beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk until well blended.
Pour mixture over bread in baking dish, turning slices to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pinwheels
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl.
Combine 1 1/2 cups of flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder; blend into the creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Add cocoa to half of the mixture and 3/4 cup of flour to the other half.
Roll each half into a square.
Place the chocolate square on top of the vanilla square and roll up.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and jellos in boiling water.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook until jelly melts and smokies are warm.

title: mom's applesauce doughnut holes
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Add applesauce and shortening; mix.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, spices and salt; mix well into applesauce mixture.
Let set to rest while heating oil.
Drop from teaspoon into hot oil to cook. The cooked doughnut hole should be about the size of an English walnut or smaller.
In paper bag, mix 1 cup sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Drop hot holes into bag; shake to coat.
Or, roll holes in powdered sugar.

title: bishop whipple pudding
directions: Beat eggs briskly. Add sugar and flour, which has been sifted with the baking powder. Add dates and nuts. Bake in 350° oven until done (pierce center with a toothpick). Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with cream or ice cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a deep dish baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: lime punch
directions: To make syrup, boil 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1 cup water and let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Crisco.
Line the bottom and sides with flour tortillas.
Brown 2 pounds hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain the fat.
Add taco mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add refried beans.

title: bonbons temptation pie(makes one 8-inch pie)
directions: Crush cookies; combine with butter.
Press into buttered 8-inch pie plate.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Spoon ice cream into pie shell.
Cover surface of ice cream with Bonbon's brand ice cream.
Freeze before serving.
Cover pie with whipped cream.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix well and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover while baking.
Serves 12.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest to creamed mixture.
Bake in a 10 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally (stirring is not a must).
Add raisins if desired.
Can be mixed the night before.

title: praline confections
directions: Line 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Then line pan with crackers.
Bring margarine and sugar to rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Stir and scrape down sides.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Spoon over crackers.
Bake in 325° oven for 18 minutes.

title: cocktail oyster crackers
directions: In a measuring cup (2 cups) put oil, dressing mix and seasonings together.
Blend.
Pour on top of crackers and keep blending until oil disappears, off and on.

title: ozzie's vegetable sauce or dip
directions: Cut thin slices of Genoa (dry) salami in quarters.
Fold double and skewer on toothpicks with a cherry-tomato half, small tomato wedge or small cube of low-calorie cheese (part skim milk Mozzarella or Neufchatel.)
One nibble with tomato, about 41 calories; with cheese, about 54 calories.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients. Don't overbeat. Don't use mixer. Bake in Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn out and cool.

title: minced clams casino
directions: Saute first eight ingredients.
Drain clams, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Simmer 1/2 cup liquid and clams for 5 minutes. Combine clams and liquid with the sauteed mixture.
Add bread crumbs and blend well.

title: winter garden
directions: Dissolve together.
Pour this mixture over a piece of coal in a saucer.
With a medicine dropper, drop a few drops of food coloring over the mixture.
Put the garden in a place where it won't be disturbed.
In a few hours tiny crystals will begin to form.
They will grow for a few days.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Drain oranges, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine juice with remaining ingredients.
Add to chops and top with oranges.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sugarless fruit nut muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine the dates, raisins and nuts; boil 5 minutes. Stir in
margarine and salt. Set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to fruit. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon into mini muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or bake in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan until tests done.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475° (very hot) about 9 p.m. the night before you are planning your meal.
Place turkey in a covered roaster pan with the onion, apple, celery and 1 quart warm water.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven but do not open oven door.
Leave all night. Your turkey will be golden brown with broth for dressing and gravy.
Tenderest turkey ever.

title: praline brunch toast
directions: In a bowl, thoroughly blend eggs, half and half, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour half of egg mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place bread slices in mixture, trimming to fit, if necessary.
Pour remaining egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lemony fish fillets
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs, lemon pepper seasoning, dill weed and garlic powder in shallow dish or on sheet of waxed paper.
Set aside.
Blend buttermilk and egg in medium bowl.
Dip fish in buttermilk mixture, then in cornflake mixture to coat.
Heat 1/8 inch Crisco oil in large skillet.
Add fish, fry 5 to 8 minutes or until flakes easily with fork.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: pancakes
directions: In blender, mix milk, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Blend well. While blending, slowly add dry ingredients.

title: mexican sunday special
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Mix meat with chili and corn.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or cast-iron skillet.
Make cornbread as directed on package, but add more liquid to make thinner.
Pour on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° until topping is done.

title: gert's peanut butter fudge #2
directions: Heat sugar, butter, syrup and milk to a boil; boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: cool salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and dry jello until well mixed.
Add cottage cheese, drained pineapple and walnuts.
Stir until well mixed. Put into dish and refrigerate until set.
(Can also decorate top with whole or crushed walnuts.)

title: munching peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir together peanuts, syrup, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Cook until mixture takes on a slight golden color.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup and cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread real thin. IF you use roasted peanuts, omit the salt and add peanuts after the first 4 minutes of cooking.
Makes about 1 pound after the brittle is broken into pieces.

title: old fashioned chocolate pies
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, glossy peaks form.
Spread over hot filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: bow tie pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, saute garlic in olive oil.
Add chicken and saute until lightly browned.
Add broccoli and saute about 4 minutes.
Add sun-dried tomatoes, basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add wine and chicken broth. Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss with bow tie pasta which has been cooked according to package directions.
Serves 6.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers, put in brine and heat, (turning cucumbers) just until they turn slightly white.
Turn off heat and pack cucumbers in jar to which a large bunch of dill has been added. Place
1 clove of garlic in jar for Kosher pickles and leave
out for plain dill pickles.
Heat bring again and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, vinegar, salt and hot sauce.
Rub into chicken and roll into bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: italian bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese atop.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 2 minutes more or until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix and refrigerate so that flavors blend.
Great for oysters or shrimp.

title: chile con queso
directions: Heat all ingredients in crock-pot and serve with any type of corn chips.

title: deep dish fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter. Remove from heat and add cocoa and hot water and stir until dissolved.
With wire whisk, blend in sugar, flour, salt, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Mix in pecans and pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Check pie by inserted knife which should come out clean.
Pie is best when served with whipped topping.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pork chops and pineapple. Place chops in a glass bowl and pour marinade over them.
Let stand for 2 to 4 hours.
Place pineapple rings on top of chops. Grill over medium coals 8 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness each side until done.
Serve with rice pilaf or fried sweet potatoes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In mixing bowl, cut lard into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in the center. Add buttermilk all at once. Stir quickly with fork just until dough follows a fork around the bowl. Divide dough in 8 pieces. Form each piece into a ball. Place in greased 9-inch pie plate. Press to flatten tops. Bake in 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 biscuits.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients; add pecans.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes (preheat oven).
Spread on greased cookie sheet to bake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Use no juice.
Mix together all ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: puto
directions: Cream shortening and add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with 6 tablespoons Carnation evaporated milk (this is a little over 1/3 cup milk). Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar (this helps keep the air in the beaten egg whites).
Fold the egg whites and pour into muffin.
Steam for about 20 minutes or until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: noah's ark clam chowder
directions: Put all ingredients into pan and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed cheese peppers
directions: Grate each cheese.
Stuff peppers with cheese, onion and pepper.
Wrap with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or grill 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese hominy
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix onion and all other ingredients except cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
May be prepared ahead.

title: rice casserole
directions: Heat together mushroom soup, chicken soup, soy sauce and water. Add rice.
Brown hamburger and bean sprouts.
Mix all together. Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
If too thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water, small amount at a time.

title: cooper's puppy chow(kid recipe)
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in saucepan until smooth (or you may melt in microwave oven).
Mix well and pour over Rice Chex cereal.
Mix together until all cereal squares are covered.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over coated cereal and mix well.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
May be pressed or rolled out. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp and mix well with other ingredients.
Chill for several hours until serving time.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix onion, soups and Ro-Tel.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish by layers:
1. chips; 2. chicken; 3. onion, soup and Ro-Tel mix and 4. cheese.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: sweet and spicy spareribs
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven over high heat, cover ribs with water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until ribs are almost tender.
Drain.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Microwave all ingredients for 1 minute (except confectioners sugar and cereal).
Pour over Chex cereal.
Put cereal and confectioners sugar in plastic bag and shake.
Store in airtight container.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth; add sugar and mix well. Add vanilla; beat until smooth.

title: crock-pot sunday supper
directions: Place contents of soup mix in a small baking dish.
Place roast in the dish and rub the mix all over it.
In 5-quart cooker, place half of the halved potatoes, carrots, celery and garlic. Mix garlic powder, thyme and pepper.
Using half of the seasoning, season the vegetables.
Mix 1 cup wine and broth; pour into slow cooker.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: basic egg pasta(pasta all' uovo)
directions: This is from Mom Campanelli.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, ground onion, red pepper and salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse in clear water twice.
Drain.
Add cornstarch, sugar, vinegar, pepper, dry mustard, celery seed, turmeric and nutmeg.
Cook slowly 30 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: old-fashioned raisin bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread, and let stand until bread is soft and cooled.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, or inserted knife comes out clean (about 1 hour and 15 minutes).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and mash out with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop by spoonfuls or roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Don't overbake; will look wet on top.

title: reduced fat herbed steak kabobs
directions: Place steak in bowl with snug fitting lid.
Combine vinegar, lime juice, oregano, onion powder, black pepper and pour over steak, turn to coat meat completely.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cook green peppers in boiling water until tender-crisp about 2 minutes; drain.
Alternately arrange steak, green pepper and mushrooms on skewers, brush with marinade.
Broil kabobs on rack 6 inches from heat source until done as desired, turning and brushing with marinade.
Place tomatoes at the end of skewers and broil until tender.
Makes 4 servings, 213 calories; 6 grams fat; 92 mg. cholesterol each.

title: dill bean sticks
directions: Snip beans.
Leave whole.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in ice water.
Pack beans in jars with dill and garlic.
Make brine with vinegar, water, salt and cayenne pepper.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: russian meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix with hands thoroughly.
Mold into loaf and place in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes until browned. Remove from baking dish and place on platter.
Cover with 1 cup tomato sauce or substitute catsup.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Put cucumbers in stone jar.
Cover with boiling water and let stand until next morning.
Drain well.
Cover with boiling water. Repeat for 3 days.
On the fifth day, drain and dry well the cucumbers.
Slice in 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine sugar, salt and vinegar.
Add spices if desired (I don't use spices).
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On third day, bring to a boil. Can and seal.
Boiling water bath is recommended. These are very good and brickel. If you have any left over, they do not turn soft.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut stew meat into thin pieces.
Brown meat and drain fat. While meat is browning, saute onions in separate pan in 1/4 cup butter.
Saute carrots, bell peppers and mushrooms each in 1/4 cup butter.
Add onions, carrots, bell peppers and mushrooms to the meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Add teriyaki sauce.
Let simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions.
Serve meat and vegetables over rice.
Serves about 4 people.
(Three pounds chicken or 2 links smoked sausage may be substituted for the stew meat.)

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra, remove ends and cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Mix cornmeal, onion salt and pepper.
Toss okra and cornmeal mixture until okra is completely covered and coated.
Cook and stir okra in vegetable oil until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, milk, margarine, eggs and sugar.
Beat on high speed with mixer until smooth.
Add flavorings.
Mix baking powder with 1 tablespoon of milk and add to the mixture. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook for
hour.
Sprinkle	1/4 cup flour over top; add water to
make
it	juicy.	Put
in casserole and top with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables until thawed; drain.
Add drained green beans.
Saute mushrooms in butter; add with cream of celery soup. If soup is thick, use small amount milk.
Mix all the preceding with 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with other half onion rings.
Serve.
Have never made this recipe without doubling.
A must at Vogler Family dinners for 44 years.

title: iris's baked oatmeal surprise
directions: Combine oil, eggs and honey. Beat well. Add oatmeal, baking powder, salt and milk. Mix. Then add apples, raisins, pecans and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: steamy onion soup
directions: Saute onions in 6 tablespoons butter in 3-quart saucepan until tender.
Do not brown.
Add beef broth and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Brown bread on both sides in remaining butter in skillet.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let cool.
Remove from pan.

title: cookie sheet apple pie
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until coarse and crumbly.
Add eggs and milk; mix into dough.
Chill 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll 1/2 to fit bottom of greased 15-inch baking pan.
Arrange apples over crust.

title: pork scallops with dijon sauce
directions: Heat half the butter and half the oil in each of 2 large, heavy skillets over medium-high heat.
Add just enough scallops to each hot skillet so they do not overlap.
(If skillet is crowded, pork will steam rather than brown.) Cook about 1 minute on each side or until browned.
Transfer the cooked scallops on a platter and cover tightly to keep warm while you cook remaining scallops. Discard fat in skillets.
Add half the wine and half the broth to each skillet; cook over high heat 1 minute, scraping up bits from bottom.
Consolidate wine/broth mixture in one skillet.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced to 1/3 cup.
Add cream and boil, uncovered, until sauce is reduced to about 3/4 cup or until it lightly coats back of spoon.
Turn off heat; whisk in mustard. Add to sauce any juices that have collected from the pork.
Pour sauce over pork or serve separately.

title: london broil
directions: Follow directions on package for mixing marinade.
With a fork, poke holes in roast on both sides.
Pour marinade over roast; let sit in refrigerator for several hours, turning often. Broil in oven or cook on grill until done.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onion in a bowl.
Sprinkle 7/8 cup sugar.
Mix vinegar, oil, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage while still boiling and let stand 4 to 6 hours.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well with pastry cutter or fork.
Beat 1 egg in measuring cup add 1 tablespoon vinegar fill with ice water to top of one cup container.
Pour this over dry ingredients blend well with for or pastry cutter.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll this into one ball and after it has chilled cut it into 4 equal sections.
Wrap each in plastic and aluminum foil then freeze till it is needed.
Each section makes one complete pie.

title: surprising salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli and chestnuts.
Dice onion and mix together.
Add other ingredients except bacon chips.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon chips on top before serving.
Very colorful.
Serves 8.

title: homemade wine
directions: Put in containers with balloon on top and tie down.
Let set for 30 days.
Strain through cheesecloth and store in bottle. Serve chilled.

title: almond white chocolate bark
directions: Toast almonds in 350° oven about 12 minutes, stir often. Cool.
Melt chocolate in double boiler, remove from heat and add almonds and apricots.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper. Refrigerate until cool and hardened.
Store up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Good at Christmas time.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant.
Dip in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil.
Take eggplant slices out when brown and put a layer in a baking dish.
Top with sauce that has been mixed with garlic, oregano, thyme and sugar. Add cheese and continue eggplant layer, sauce and cheese until finished.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until cheese browns.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Add celery, onions, pepper and pimento. Marinate several hours in dressing in refrigerator.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt together cheese and butter on medium heat; stir continually.
Sift two boxes sugar and cocoa together.
Pour liquid mixture over dry mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Spread evenly.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Eat and enjoy.

title: fruit solid
directions: You poot in some grapes, ornges, apples, pineapple, pars, bananas, strawbers and wipe cream.
Stir together.
Put it in your mouth and eat it.
Say yummy!

title: ice box cookies
directions: Work all ingredients together and roll into logs.
Wrap in plastic wrap and place in ice box.
Slice cookies off log as needed and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes or until brown.
Wrap unused portion tightly with plastic and store in refrigerator.

title: frozen passion
directions: In an ice cream freezer, combine ingredients.
Mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: chocolate tipped butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetables(served as a salad, side dish or appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients except vegetables together.
Cook each vegetable separately, about 35 minutes.
When done, cool 15 minutes.
Place in marinade; chill 4 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour the mayonnaise mixture over broccoli; mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Ready to eat.

title: steak marinade
directions: Sprinkle both sides of steak with each ingredient.
Pierce steak several times with fork.
Marinate for 6 hours in the refrigerator.
Grill until desired doneness.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients.
Loosely form teaspoon size balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown (approximately 20 minutes).

title: cantonese dinner
directions: Brown pork in oil to remove excess fat; drain.
Place pork and all other ingredients in crock-pot, 6 to 8 hours on low or 3 hours on high.
Serve over rice.
Can be made stovetop.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop vegetables; mix well.
Put a layer of vegetables in an enameled pan or stone jar and sprinkle with salt.
Repeat until all vegetables are used.
Cover the last layer with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
In separate vessel, put vinegar, sugar, ground mustard, mustard seed, celery seed and cloves.
Heat to boiling; add the well drained vegetables and cook slowly until tender (about 30 minutes).
Pack in jars.
Process in boiling water bath canner for 10 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix beef with salsa, egg, taco powder and bread crumbs.
Form into loaf pan.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top so it covers all of the meat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook for 35 minutes. Enjoy!

title: sesame-cheese dip mix
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream in a small bowl; blend well.
Once blended, mix with sour cream.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: rosemary focaccia
directions: In a large bowl, or the bowl of an electric mixer, combine the warm water, yeast and sugar; let proof until foamy.
Stir in 1/3 of the flour, the olive oil less 2 tablespoons (reserve for brushing), 1 teaspoon salt and the rosemary and scallions.
Either by hand or in an electric mixer fitted with a dough-hook attachment, gradually incorporate the remaining flour until dough forms a slightly sticky ball (it could require more or less flour).
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic.
Form dough into a ball and let rise in a covered, oiled bowl for about 1 hour or until dough doubles in size.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture. Add nuts.
Place in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Good with powdered sugar frosting.
Serves 5 to 10.

title: rice casserole
directions: Simmer margarine, pepper and onions until tender.
Add mushrooms, cream cheese and rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Spray baking dish with Pam.)

title: tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Mix with hands.
Add water a little at a time.
Knead well.
Pinch off golf-ball size ball of dough and roll out a circle 1/8-inch thick.
Cook on grill over medium heat approximately 1 minute on each side.
Test doneness.
Pinch edge until no longer sticky to touch.
To reheat, place directly over low fire and turn often.

title: yummy cornbread
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add hot grease.
Bake at 425-450° until done.
Can be baked in muffin pans and this recipe makes 24 small muffins.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix sugars, egg yolks and flour.
Add milk and water, a little at a time, until all mixed well.
Add salt.
Cook in doubler boiler until thick.
Add butter and vanilla; mix good.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: veal scaloppine velez
directions: Dip each veal escalope first into flour, then into the beaten eggs, then into a mixture of the bread crumbs, salt, pepper, thyme and basil.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet.
Saute the escalopes over high heat about 2 1/2 minutes on each side.
Top each escalope with 2 ounces ham and 2 asparagus spears.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and place under preheated broiler just until cheese melts.
Garnish with tomato wedges and green olives.
Serves 8.

title: galleria chicken cutlets
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Mix eggs and water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in crumbs. Heat oil and brown chicken.
Remove to a greased baking dish. Spoon mushrooms over chicken.
Melt butter and add lemon juice. Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chili for hot dogs
directions: Put meat in enough water to make a thick mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop all vegetables small to fill Corelle bowl size or cereal bowl size.
Cook spaghetti; rinse well with cold water.
Add vegetables; mix well.
Add Salad Supreme; mix well.
Add salad dressing; mix well.

title: meat and rice casserole(microwave)
directions: In
a 3 quart dish crumble ground beef.
Cover with wax paper and
cook on High for 6 minutes.
Drain grease and stir meat.
If pink is showing, cook another 3 to 4 minutes on High until pink is gone.
Drain again.

title: pedernales river chili
directions: *Chili meat is coarsely ground round steak or well-trimmed chuck.
If specially ground, ask butcher to use 3/4-inch plate for coarse grind.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese (add a drop of milk to make creamy).
Spread on regular size dinner plate.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Then top with green peppers, tomatoes, onion and last of all grated cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip(yields 1 large mold)
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Stir in cream cheese.
When cheese is melted, remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup of water. Add onion, celery and mayonnaise to soup mixture. Stir in gelatine.
Pour into greased mold.
Chill until firm.
Best made the day before.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread into a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter in a saucepan.
Melt cheese, then add mushroom soup and all other ingredients.
Serve in chafing dish.
Serve with corn chips.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and stir.
Mix in sugar, flour, nutmeg and rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 24 hour cabbage salad
directions: Bring the last 4 ingredients to a full boil; pour over cabbage, onions, pepper and carrots and let stand overnight. Keeps good in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Make into balls; roll in sugar and flatten out with fork.

title: celery and apple stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly together.
Can be used for stuffing pork, fish or poultry.
Very tasty!

title: almond crescent cookies
directions: Finely grind almonds in blender.
Mix 1 2/3 cups of almonds with flour, sugar, butter and vanilla extract (set remaining almonds aside).
Form ball; chill 1 hour or overnight.
Roll dough into small ball and then longways to form crescents.
Roll in remaining almonds.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350° (cookies should be light brown).
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Mix milk with pudding.
Layer in punch bowl as follows: 1/2 of cake pieces, 1/2 of pudding, 1 1/2 cans pie filling, 1/2 bananas and 1/2 crushed pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: frozen lemon mousse
directions: Freeze milk until icy.
Whip milk until thick and fluffy.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Save a little rind for the topping.
Place in buttered pan lined with vanilla wafers.
Sprinkle grated rind on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour and stir well into a roue. Gradually add broth and broccoli.
Cook on medium heat until broccoli is tender, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and stir in milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Yield: 4 cups soup.

title: bombay chicken
directions: Skin fat from chicken pieces.
In a 5-quart pot, heat 4 tablespoonfuls
oil
and fry onions until browned.
Remove and set aside.
In
the same oil, fry coconut.
Now add the chicken, onions,
ginger
and
garlic
and fry until the chicken is slightly brown.
Do all this on moderate heat, adding a little more
oil if necessary.
Now add the yogurt, tomatoes, cloves, cardamon, cumin, coriander and peppercorn powder.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Now
add
the
nutmeg,
cinnamon
and paprika.
Stir thoroughly,
reduce
heat
to
low and simmer until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle fresh chopped coriander leaves on top before serving.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: olive oil dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour over greens.

title: oatmeal chocolate chippers
directions: Thoroughly
cream
together shortening, brown and white sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to
creamed
mixture,
mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts
and chocolate
chips.
Drop
heaping
teaspoonfuls
on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with fork or bottom of glass. Bake
at
375° for
8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on rack. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: easy chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.
Pie will be a little shaky in the middle when done.
The pecans will rise to the top when cooking and form a "meringue."

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil, eggs, preserves and cherries together and set aside.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon, cocoa and nuts.
Pour half batter into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture and cut into batter (swirl with a fork).
Pour rest of batter in pan and sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Cut into batter again.
bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
(Freezes well.)

title: one minute chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Boil exactly 1 minute.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Dice rhubarb into 1/2 inch pieces.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and Jell-O.
Pour over diced rhubarb; toss until pieces are thoroughly coated.
Put into 9-inch pie crust (unbaked) and bake 10 minutes at 450° and about 30 minutes at 350°.
While pie is still warm, sprinkle top crust with sugar.

title: baked cheese fries
directions: Put fries in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix soups and milk. Place cheese, onions and seasonings over potatoes.
Pour in soup and milk.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: overnight chicken or tuna casserole(microwave)
directions: Whisk
soup
and milk until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover
and
refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Cover and microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: In saucepan, mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from burner and cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating while slowly pouring cooled mixture into egg whites.
Spread over cooled pie filling, sealing edges.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make 1-inch balls.
Cook in microwave for 10 minutes, or until done.
Add to any pasta or can be used in stroganoff, also.

title: apricot surprise
directions: In saucepan, mix jello, sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Cut cream cheese in small pieces.
Mix in Gerber apricots with tapioca and fold in Cool Whip (need a large bowl).
Stir in pineapple mixture when cool.
Chill before serving.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Save out 1 cup small cauliflower pieces.
Cook chicken broth with vegetables until tender.
Put in food processor and blend. Add cheese to soup and pepper if desired.
Saute the 1 cup raw cauliflower in butter or steam just until tender.
Add to soup and serve.

title: apple crunch muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients for muffins. Cut in shortening. Mix in egg and milk. Stir in shredded apple. Do not overmix (batter should be lumpy). Pour batter into 12 greased muffin tins. Mix the brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon for the crunch topping; sprinkle over the muffins. Bake at 400°F. for about 25 minutes.

title: special "hors d'oeuvres"
directions: Precook bacon (brown but limp).
Unroll crescents and place on tinfoil lined cookie sheet. Spread 2 slices of bacon and approximately 1/2 cup cheese on each crescent.
Roll crescent with ingredients inside.
Bake until golden brown in a 325° oven for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: green beans with shallot butter
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter with oil in a small skillet.
Add shallots and cook 7-9 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally, until very tender.
Stir in remaining butter, the salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Cook beans uncovered in a large pot of water 5-7 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Add shallot butter and parsley.
Toss to mix and coat.
You can make the shallot butter up to 5 days ahead.
Makes 15 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic.
Mix all ingredients with macaroni and cheese mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken and bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Add all ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs and butter together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut, chopped walnuts and can of sweetened condensed milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 24 bars.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in large saucepan.
Cook on medium-high until soft ball stage (when dropped in cup of cool water, you can pick it up and roll into ball).
Stir constantly. When reaches soft ball stage, take off heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until thick.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole. Combine broth, soup, milk and relish. Layer half of tortillas, chicken soup mix, onion and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese. Best if refrigerated 24 hours before baking. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry sausage and beef with onions and spices; drain off all grease.
Add grated or chipped up cheese.
Mix all together until cheese is all melted.
Spread on slices of bread approximately 2 tablespoons to each slice.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.

title: orange pecan bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add milk, orange juice and egg; mix only until dry ingredients are dampened.
Add rind and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let sit 20 minutes before baking 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before turning out on rack to cool.
Store overnight before cutting.

title: deer sage sausage
directions: Place all into a bowl and mix thoroughly, using your hands to shape into patties.
Fry patties until brown on both sides and well done.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan
and
add the onion and bell pepper; cook until	they
soften.
Prepare casserole dish with Pam.
In mixing bowl,
add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion soup and cream of chicken soup, plus
one can of water.
Blend well and add rice, shrimp
and
softened
onion,
pepper and margarine. Mix well and pour
into
prepared
dish.
Cover
with foil and place in preheated oven for one hour at 350°.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Crust:
Press rolls in the bottom of a rectangular shaped pan. Bake as directed on package.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer until creamy.
Serve with fresh fruit salad.
(Instead of milk, can add 2 T. fresh orange juice and 1/2 tsp. pure orange extract.)

title: lemon supreme special
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Next add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour in oven.

title: mareta's festive baba
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch ring mold generously.
Make cake mix according to package directions.
Fill pan half full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; unmold while hot.
While the cake is baking, mix grenadine, water and rum.
Heat and dribble slowly and evenly over hot cake.
Puree and heat apricot preserves; spread over cake.
Sprinkle with finely chopped candied fruit.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: curried fruit(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Butter baking dish and dust with flour.
Arrange fruit in dish and spread with butter/sugar mixture over all.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Shred cheese and set aside.
Make crumbs out of bread.
In a large frypan melt butter over medium heat.
Add crumbs and lemon peel.
Cook crumbs until brown.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer broccoli and cheese.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding mix, sour cream, Cool Whip and milk. Layer wafers and bananas and cover with pudding mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each.
Add milk and coconut flavoring. Sift dry ingredients. Add to mixture.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in a tube pan in a cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: little red chick
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan, except mushrooms and bouillon.
Pour mixture over uncooked chicken.
You can place in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Place in 350° oven, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and dissolved bouillon cube; cook another 30 minutes. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into two large or four small, lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top will crack.

title: lobster newburg(low-fat)
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir half of hot mixture into the beaten egg; return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Do not boil.
Stir in lobster, dry sherry and peppers; heat through. Serve over muffin halves.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients and spread out in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: strawberry delight salad
directions: In mixing bowl, put Jell-O and 2 cups hot water.
Mix.
Add frozen berries.
Mix thoroughly.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Stir.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square dish or pan.
Refrigerate until solid.
Cover with thin layer of sour cream.
(Refrigerate until solid before covering with the sour cream.)

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; mash potatoes.
Drain pineapple and mix with potatoes.
Use your hands and form ball with potatoes around marshmallows.
Roll balls in shredded coconut.
Bake in buttered dish for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Put the dry ingredients in a gallon zip lock freezer bag, this recipe can be stored in refrigerator until you want to make up a batch of cookies.
When ready to make cookies combine 3 c. mix with the eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Dip in pwd. sugar while hot.

title: texas sheet cake - brownies
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and cold water.
Pour over the flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; beat and pour into a large rimmed cookie sheet, 10 x 15-inch at least.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Last 5 minutes of baking time, make icing.

title: meat loaf and sauce
directions: Mix in bowl, beef, eggs, crackers, pepper, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Form into very firm loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal mixture and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with topping.

title: city chicken
directions: Push meat cubes onto skewers.
Combine cracker and corn flake crumbs and seasonings.
In separate dish, combine egg and milk. Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Brown slowly on all sides in hot fat (oil or shortening).
Dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube in 3/4 cup hot water.
Add to meat.
Cover tightly; simmer one hour or until tender or place in baking dish and cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini into 1/2-inch pieces, put in boiling water. Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Saute onion and peppers in oil, add spaghetti sauce, Cheddar cheese, mushrooms, paste and water.
Mix well and pour over zucchini. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook in microwave for 13 minutes, turning pan once.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients together and bake in a roaster at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil 5 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla, chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Pour into pan and let cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onions together.
Do not drain. Do not drain beans.
Stir all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings in a large skillet until tender.
Drain tomatoes with chiles, reserving juice.
Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Add tomatoes with chiles, chopped green chiles, salt and pepper to onion.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 15 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Thin cheese mixture to desired consistency by adding reserved tomato liquid, one tablespoon at a time.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: worlds best sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine. Add oil, eggs, and vanilla. Mix well. Add soda, salt, cream of tartar and mix well. Roll into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet. Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes; add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and flour.
Stir and add baking soda and cinnamon.
Line a jelly roll pan with wax paper and grease paper.
Pour in the cake, spreading evenly, and sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife and turn over onto tea towel that has been sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Roll towel and cool for 20 minutes.
Unroll and spread filling, then re-roll.

title: snowballs
directions: Shape ice cream balls.
Roll in flaked coconut.
Freeze until very firm.
Remove from freezer one at a time and decorate with icings and gels to resemble Christmas tree ornaments or decorate with flowers. Use simple designs and work quickly.
Return each snowball to freezer when finished.

title: baked pineapple with brown sugar and kahlua
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange pineapple in a single layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Drizzle Kahlua over.
Bake until pineapple juice bubbles, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizzette(small fried pizza with sauce)
directions: Place flour in large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in one tablespoon lukewarm water.
Add flour.
Gradually add remaining water to flour, mixing until firm, elastic dough forms.
Knead for a few minutes.
Form into ball.
Let rise for about 2 hours.
Place tomatoes in a saucepan with a little salt and the sugar.
Cook over medium heat until softened and the liquid has evaporated. Chop garlic with chili pepper.
Saute in olive oil until garlic is lightly colored.
Stir into tomato sauce and keep hot.
Roll dough into log.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Roll out each piece on floured work surface.
Heat oil in cast-iron skillet, fry pizzas, turning over until each is puffy and light brown.
Drain pizzas onto paper towels.
Transfer to serving platter.
Add the basil to the tomato sauce.
Serve sauce with pizzas. Garnish with basil sprigs.

title: broccoli marinade
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Cut the broccoli into flowerets.
Slice the red onion.
Mix all ingredients together. Allow to marinate for approximately 2 hours.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Use only the young sprouts, 6 or 8-inches high. Do not cut below surface of the ground as the root is poisonous.
Parboil leaves and stalks 3 times, pouring off water after each 1 minute of boiling.
Boil in fourth water until thoroughly tender. Drain and fry in hot, salted bacon drippings.
Serve with vinegar.

title: cheese celery sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Spread into celery stalks.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: barbecue beef cups
directions: Press biscuits into muffin tins.
Brown hamburger; drain fat. Add chopped onion and sauce.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese.
Makes 10 cups.

title: tijuana bean dip(fat-free)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwavable dish, combine beans, cheese, green onions and jalapeno peppers.
Cover with wax paper; microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato, salsa and lemon juice.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: chicken delight
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.	Place dried beef on bottom of dish.
Wrap each piece of chicken with bacon slice.
Place over beef.
In separate bowl, mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: are you married? cake
directions: Beat together the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil, and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in the sour cream, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool at least one hour and top with powdered sugar (use a strainer to shake it on).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Pour into large baking dish and mix in soup.
Spread over bottom of dish and add cheese slices.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: grandma d's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix sausage, croutons and milk in a bowl. Fill mushroom caps and bake at 350° until hot on cookie sheet.

title: doris' hot dog relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in a big pot until thick. Put in several jars and seal.
Keeps all winter long.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will need a flowerpot and artificial flower.

title: company broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with onion rings.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: baked beans(with meat)
directions: Fry bacon and hamburger; drain.
Combine beans and meat in crock-pot or roasting pan.
Combine catsup and brown sugar in small bowl; mix well.
Add mixtures together; heat thoroughly in crock-pot for 1 hour or in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Gently stir several times during refrigeration

title: whiskey cake
directions: Cut cherries into halves.
Soak cherries and raisins in whiskey overnight.

title: nutty sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft, about 45 minutes.
Peel and mash. Mix together with the remaining ingredients and put into casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix well.
Place in greased baking dish and add topping.

title: cavitini
directions: Brown the sausage and drain.
Add pepperoni, green pepper and onion.
Saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Add seasoning, tomato paste, water and oil.
Blend well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooked noodles (any type will do; I use mostaccioli noodles).
Blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Put 1 can cherry pie filling on top.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Salt pork chops and dip in flour.
Brown in electric fryer. Add onion and mushroom soups; cover and simmer for 1 hour at 250°.

title: meaty spinach manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in the flour until smooth. Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted; set aside.
Drain manicotti; set aside.
In a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Add the chicken, spinach, eggs, Mozzarella cheese and 3/4 cup white sauce. Stuff into manicotti shells.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce each into two ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Top with manicotti.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over the top.
Reheat the remaining white sauce, stirring constantly.
Pour over spaghetti sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.
Yield: 14 to 16 servings.

title: red sauce
directions: Mix well and store 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together, then chill 10 minutes.
Roll in chopped nuts (pecans or walnuts) and make ball.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nancy's pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops.
Place chops on top of rice.
Mix soups and pour on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: wheat germ zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugars and flavoring and beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine flour, wheat germ, soda, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture until blended.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add onion, green beans, tomato sauce and brown gravy.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Boil and cream potatoes or prepare instant potatoes.
Add 1 egg to creamed potatoes.
Top hamburger mixture with scoops of potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts (about 30 minutes).

title: jean kiraly's oven-baked pancakes
directions: You will need 2 round cake pans or 1 (10 x 13-inch) pan.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Heat sauce in medium saucepan.
Warm tortillas in microwave to soften.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine dry soup mix with sour cream and mayonnaise and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add several shakes of curry powder.

title: pan fish bordeaux style
directions: On top of the stove, saute the onions in 2 tablespoons of butter using an ovenproof dish that can go to the table later. When the onions begin to turn golden brown, add the walnuts and mushrooms and stir well.
Next, place the fish on top of the ingredients in the pan.
Sprinkle with the salt and pepper. Combine the wine and Fish Stock and pour over them.
Close the pan and transfer it to a preheated 300° oven.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Heat oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add flour, stirring constantly on medium heat until medium brown, about 30 minutes. Add onion and cook for 10 minutes.
Add celery, parsley, bell pepper, green onions and then water.
Add seasoned chicken and sausage.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 2 hours or until the gumbo tastes done.
Be sure it's seasoned to your taste. Serve in bowl topped with cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Put corn and flour into mixing bowl.
Cut margarine into pieces.
Pour whipping cream straight from carton.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ever so easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Sift together flour and baking soda; set aside. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out of pan. Cool completely.
Glaze and garnish as desired.

title: quick pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Add salt, flour, juice from pineapple and flavorings; mix well.
Add water, a little at a time, until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.

title: cheese pretzels
directions: Cut cheese into pieces.
Place cheese, cream and Tabasco into a casserole.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir smooth each minute. Dip half of pretzel into cheese.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Place on waxed paper until firm.

title: bev coney's tasty tidbits
directions: Place 2 squares of the almond bark in a small bowl and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
(Microwave 25 seconds longer, if necessary, to obtain creamy consistency.)
Drop crackers in melted almond bark; coat completely.
Use knife to slide onto wax paper.
Let set.
That's all folks . . .
and you'll be surprised how quickly they disappear!

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook meat until done (1 hour).
Add diced onion and cabbage. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to own taste.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt Crisco in 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: homemade salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Cook patties over medium heat in skillet, a few at a time, until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in rest of soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat and cook on low heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, turning until done.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine ham, broccoli and onion.
Put in the bottom of pie shell. Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and Swiss cheese.
Pour over mixture already in bottom of the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious salad
directions: Mix dry gelatin and cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Fold in whipped topping and chill.

title: bakery frosting
directions: Beat
together
shortening,
flavoring, salt and water, but only until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in sugar, 1/3 box at a time.
Beat only until well blended.

title: two-cheese scalloped potatoes(reduced fat recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine milk, 3/4 c. cheddar, 1/2 c. Monterey Jack, ketchup, Worcestershire and pepper; set aside. Arrange half of potatoes and half of onion in the bottom of a 13 X 9 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Top with half of milk mixture. Repeat layers; top with 3/4 c. cheddar, 1/2 c. Monterey Jack, and parsley. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover; bake an additional 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender and cheese is browned.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit on paper towels.
Mix butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken-n-cheese casserole
directions: Cook chicken at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes). Cook Rice-A-Roni according to box directions, but use College Inn chicken broth instead of water.
Steam chopped carrots until cooked (approximately 20 minutes).
Crush Ritz crackers into bits. Cut up cooked chicken.

title: creamy fruit delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly to prevent milk from curdling.
Stir in evaporated skimmed milk.
Chill until as thick as unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in fruit.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan or 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with additional fruit.
Makes 7 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: strawberry impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender as given, except strawberries. Blend at high speed for 10 seconds.
Place mixture into a well-greased 10-inch glass plate.
Drop strawberries on top (do not push down).
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° until golden brown. When done, you will have crust on the bottom, custard in the middle and a coconut topping.
Refrigerate. You can substitute different fruit, such as cherries or peaches.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak dried apricots for 20 minutes.
Cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and eggs.
