Dissolve sugar in orange juice and add to above.
Add dry ingredients, blend well.
Drain apricots; stir apricots and nuts into batter.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan 8 x 5-inch for 65 minutes or until done.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa at a hard boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Beat together until it starts to thicken.
Then place bite size spoonfuls onto wax paper or cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Yield: approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: holiday pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over the top of cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin. Slice onions and peppers; combine with cucumbers and salt. Let stand for 3 hours. Drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large pot. Bring to boil. Add drained cucumbers; heat thoroughly but do not boil. Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal. (Use pickling spices tied in cheesecloth.)

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles and Cheddar cheese, in skillet; heat.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Shred Cheddar cheese.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can make ahead of time and refrigerate before cooking.
(Do not put directly in oven from refrigerator.)

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into three 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Tear bread into cubes and place in buttered 8 or 9-inch square baking dish or 8 x 12-inch pan.
Dot with butter.
Drain sauerkraut well, squeezing out liquid.
Place over bread crumbs. Crumble corned beef and mix with sour cream, mayonnaise and catsup.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place cheese triangles on top of casserole and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oil, water, lemon flavoring and egg yolks until smooth.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff and dry (about 5 minutes).
Fold into flour mixture and pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour in preheated 300° oven.
Remove from oven and invert pan over a bottle to cool for at least 1 hour.
May be glazed.

title: diabetic sugarless apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons brown Sugar Twin or Sprinkle Sweet.

title: pear or apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; folding in apples last.
Bake at 350°
about 1 hour.
This makes a good Bundt cake.
I use cream cheese frosting.

title: pour pizza
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, pepper, oregano, eggs and milk; pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with hamburg and pizza sauce.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes; 400° for 20 minutes, 10 minutes longer at 350° with cheese.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Finely chop the shrimp and water chestnuts together.
Beat the eggs, then beat in the shrimp mixture, salt, sugar, sherry, scallions and cornstarch.
This can be done in a food processor. Remove the crusts from the bread and cut each slice into 4 triangles.
Spread each triangle with the shrimp mixture.
In a large skillet, heat oil 1-inch deep to 375°.
Put in the triangles shrimp side down and cook until they are lightly browned.
(These cook fast so don't overload frying pan.)
Turn and cook until the toast is golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep Shrimp Toast warm in a 200° oven until ready to serve.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water; stir until shortening is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt and beat in cold water. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Combine 3 mixtures and add flour.
If dough is too soft to hold shape, add 1/4 cup more flour.
Cover and let stand in warm place 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls and allow to rise until double again. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: weight watcher salad
directions: Chill fruit and drain before mixing together.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add dry Jell-O last; stir and let stand in refrigerator for about 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Take the one egg (beaten) and 1 pound can of fruit cocktail (drained) and add to the first four ingredients; mix.

title: smothered steak
directions: Pour cans of soup in a slow cooker.
Add several cans of water and stir.
Set temperature at 350° to heat.
Cut, flour and brown meat in a frypan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add browned meat to the hot soup.
Make sure meat is covered with soup.
Turn temperature to simmer, cover and cook 12 to 24 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir and add water as needed.

title: favorite icing
directions: Melt the ingredients, cool and add vanilla to suit taste.
Mix in powdered sugar until right consistency to spread.
This icing will not be sticky and does not have a powdered sugar taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda and oats.
Mix well; add raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: bacon wrapped scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pan.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Roll scallops in seasoned flour mixture.
Shake off excess.
Dip into egg, then coat with bread crumbs; cover well.
Wrap in bacon strips and secure with toothpick.
Put on baking dish.
Bake until bacon is crisp and scallops are done good, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with cocktail sauce.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in thin slices.
Heat oil in large frypan.
Add beef and stir over high heat until meat is brown.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, beef broth, green pepper, celery and onion.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are done, then add cornstarch, water and soy sauce that has been blended to thicken meat mixture.
Serves 4.

title: garden pesto(heart healthy)
directions: Chop the basil, garlic and pine nuts in a food processor. With the motor running, drizzle in the oil. Blend in the cheese, salt and pepper. Refrigerate, covered, for up to 3 days. Makes about 1 cup. Serve over pasta or use with cooking chicken or pork.

title: crock-pot mostaccioli
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Form into meatballs. Brown the meatballs in a skillet; set aside.
Cut Italian sausage into 1 1/2-inch pieces; brown in the skillet until cooked through. Set aside with meatballs to drain.
Place all the remaining ingredients, except pasta, into the crock-pot.
When placing the remaining raw ground beef in crock-pot, break it into small pieces with your hands.
Mix well.
Add meatballs and sausage.
Mix well again.
Set crock-pot on low setting for 7 to 8 hours or medium setting for 4 1/2 hours.
When done, skim grease off top, as desired.
Stir in cooked mostaccioli and mix well.
Top with freshly grated Parmesan Reggiano cheese to taste.

title: low cost casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese mix according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased two quarter casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
This is so easy even the kids can fix it!
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Roll into small balls. Dip into sugar.
Press down on greased baking sheet, using base of a drinking glass to flatten.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend flour; mix with batter until real soft.
After blended, add 1 tablespoon water and 1 tablespoon Lea & Perrins.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Put on top rack of oven.

title: joe ida cookies(church cookies)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugars and vanilla.
Add milk and cream alternately with flour (save 2 cups flour).
Add softened lard (I beat lard with eggbeater until smooth).
Add rest of flour and soda, baking powder and salt.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix enchilada sauce, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and water together.
Bring to a boil and mix with ground beef.
Place a layer of chips in pan.
Slice cheese on chips and pour sauce on top and continue to layer.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes, until brown on top.

title: speedy baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to
400°.	Spray baking pan with vegetable Pam spray.
Wash
and
cut
potatoes lengthwise.
Place halves cut side down on
pan.	Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, carrots and celery with water.
Add chicken bouillon cubes.
Cook slowly until potatoes are tender, but not mushy.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat Pet milk before adding to other ingredients.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all together, except flour.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Let set overnight, if possible.

title: chinese beets
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat, or until mixture thickens.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Serve with cottage cheese, chop in salads or eat plain.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Blend oil and egg into apple mixture.
Combine dry ingredients and add to apples, mixing well.
Pour into oiled 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick to see if it is done.
Let cool 10 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, vanilla and milk until smooth. Add more milk, if needed.
Then add food coloring.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown together meat and onion.
Line greased 13 x 9-inch pan with 1/2 of tortillas.
Pour in meat and onion mixture.
Add beans, enchilada sauce and soup.
Top with 1/2 grated cheese and another layer of tortillas.
Pour tomatoes and peppers over all. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine vegetables; stir in dressing. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit pectin in Dutch oven. Bring to boil, boil 6 minutes; stirring frequently.
Stir in fruit pectin.
Continue boiling for 3 additional minutes, stirring frequently.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry beef with onion.
Add to remaining ingredients except last 3. Simmer 30 minutes on low.
Serve with tortilla chips, sour cream and shredded cheese.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Pour boiling water of apples.
Mix sugar, flour and coconut together; put this over apples.
Cut butter over apple mixture and cook about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mini balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into walnut size meatballs. Chill 1 hour.
Fry 3 minutes or until done.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture with toothpick. Place on waxed paper until chocolate is firm.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and 2 c. sugar until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each additional.
Combine flour baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture alternating with sour cream, beating just enough after each addition to keep batter smooth. Spoon one third of batter into greased 10 inch tube pan.
Combine cinnamon, nuts and remaining sugar, sprinkle 1/3 over batter in pan.
Repeat layers two more times.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes until done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to a wire rack to cool.
16-20 servings

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip in 9 inch pie plate.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle with grated cheese to taste.
Garnish with tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: number 8 french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
water
and add salt and sugar.
Add rest of
ingredients.
Knead
for
a
few minutes on a floured surface. Grease the
Dutch oven and put in dough.
Place in a warm spot and
let
rise.
When
it rises to the top, put in a 350° oven and bake
until
done.
It will be golden brown and have a hollow sound.
Let cool and serve.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Drop by teapoon on ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: fay nielsen's fresh mushroom casserole
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes in butter.
Remove from heat and add green pepper, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put in 1/2 of the bread and add vegetable mixture, then remaining bread.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix soup, can of mushrooms and cheese and add to casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Use upper shelf of oven and put a cookie sheet under casserole.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups of boiling water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries with juice and pineapple with juice.
Pour half the jello mixture in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Slice bananas on top of jello. Spread sour cream over bananas and jello. Pour remaining jello over top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed graham cracker crumbs, sugar and 3/4 cup melted oleo.
(Half the graham cracker crumbs may be substituted with Oreo crumbs.)
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana date nut bars
directions: Mash small banana in mixing bowl.
Add cake mix and 1/4 cup water.
Mix 3 minutes.

Add balance of water and mix 1 minute. Pour batter into lightly greased 10-inch square baking pan (one 8-inch square and one 8 x 4-inch pan can be used instead). Sprinkle batter with 1/2 cup chopped dates and 1/4 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut bars in pan.
Makes 2 dozen bars, 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch, 58 calories per bar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans in salted water or in water with bacon drippings, ham bone or salt pork.
Add onion, garlic, celery, pepper and bay leaf and continue cooking until done, about 3 hours.
Place dry rice on plate and top with beans which should be fairly soupy. Serves 4.

title: bea golden's moist cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add the rest of ingredients and beat vigorously.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Let cool completely and spread icing over it.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Make 1 crust; sprinkle with flour and sugar mixture.
Place apples in crust; if tart, add more sugar.
Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Pour on cream; sprinkle on cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 425° until apples are done in the middle.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic until brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: banana pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs and combine with cornstarch, sugar and salt.
In a double boiler, pour milk over cornstarch mixture; cook approximately 6 minutes or until thick.
Arrange alternate layers of wafers and bananas in bowl and pour custard over these.
Eat warm or cool.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift flour with spices; add to sugar mixture.
Mix in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful (about the size of a walnut).
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Put ribs in large shallow pan. Add onions, season with salt and pepper. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Drain off excess drippings. Saute garlic and onion in butter. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until smooth. Coat ribs with sauce and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours longer, turning and basting every 20 minutes until tender.

title: mary sims paprika potatoes
directions: Select new red potatoes about the size of golf balls if possible.
Scrub
well
and
boil
in salted water until done. Melt
a
stick
of	oleo
in Pyrex dish and set aside.
Remove peelings
from
potatoes and roll in melted oleo until coated. Place
in Pyrex dish, sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy fudge
directions: In double boiler, add vanilla, Eagle Brand milk, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips; cook until all melted.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts, chopped.
In pan sprayed with Pam, spread 1/2 cup walnuts in pan.
Add fudge mixture and add 1/2 cup walnuts to top, pressing into fudge.
Set in the refrigerator.
After it sets, cut in squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt oleo and blend in flour.
Add stock, then milk.
Stir until thickened (heating on low-medium heat).
Add chicken, seasonings and vegetables.
Put into a casserole.
Cover with biscuit dough or pastry rolled thin.
Brush top with butter.
Bake in oven at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: corn flake holly
directions: Heat marshmallows and oleo on low heat until melted.
Mix in vanilla, almond and food coloring.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add corn flakes and gently stir until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Add red cinnamon candies to center to give appearance of holly with berries.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pork chop spanish rice
directions: In large Dutch oven, slowly brown the chops in heated oil. Drain off excess oil.
Sprinkle chops with salt, chili powder and black pepper.
Add rice, onion and chopped green peppers.
Pour in tomatoes and juice.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add pepper rings and cook 2 minutes longer or until rice and meat are tender.
Arrange on serving platter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with pepper rings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; cream.
Stir in flour, salt and soda after mixing the 3 dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash with onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into a 1 1/2- quart casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve bubbling hot.

title: pineapple pistachio salad
directions: Gently fold all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwaved chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts with wooden mallet between 2 pieces of waxed paper until about 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese on each.
Tuck in sides and roll up as for jelly roll.
Skewer with toothpicks.

title: professional frosting(excellent for decorating cakes or christmas cookies)
directions: Boil water and sugar together a few minutes.
Put powdered sugar in large bowl and make a deep well.
Add egg whites and start beating, then add sugar mixture gradually while beating. Then start adding Crisco and flavoring, carefully.
Beat like whipping cream.
Can also color with food coloring to make designs, flowers, etc.
Keeps up to three weeks in refrigerator. If too thick, add water a tablespoon at a time until it's like whipping cream.
If too thin, just add powdered sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large mixing bowl; add oil, eggs, pineapple, pecans and carrots.
Mix well but do not beat vigorously.
Bake at 350° in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: orange cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well combined.
Use as a spread also on whole wheat bread, crackers or pumpkin bread.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Mix all together well.
Turn out on paper with a lot of flour and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl and put bowl in plastic bag and refrigerate.
When ready to use pinch off amount you need and place on floured paper and knead a few times.
Cut into biscuits.
Turn biscuits in greased pan and bake in 400° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add dates, nuts and cherries.
Drop by teaspoon into crushed corn flakes.
Shape into balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet and top with 1/2 of a cherry.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Fry ground meat and onion until done.
Mix sauces, soups and chilies; add to meat.
Layer in the bottom of a casserole dish, the meat first, then the cheese, then raw tortillas.
Repeat 2 or 3 times, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until mixture bubbles and cheese is melted.

title: husky cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream together the cheese, butter, salt and pepper. Add flour.
Make into roll. Wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator. Will keep a month. When needed, slice into thin wafers and bake on a greased cookie sheet for approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften, then cream.
Add marshmallow cream. Blend well, then add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of pineapple, bananas, melons, strawberries, etc.

title: blair's incredible sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together in large bowl.
Beat eggs into mixture.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar and cheese.
Add onion, oil, eggs, milk and corn.
Mix well.
Fold in peppers.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, well greased, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together flour with 1 cup of milk.
Add to macaroni and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add remaining 2 cups of milk and sprinkle with extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press center slightly, forming indentation.
Fill with jelly and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit cake
directions: mix eggs, sugar, bourbon, vanilla, butter and baking powder - blend well.
Mix chopped candied fruit and nuts together and pour plain flour over fruit and nuts and dredge until each piece is coated with flour.
Then pour mixed liquid over floured fruit and nuts and mix well.
Pour mixture into greased pan and bake for 3 hours in
250 degrees oven.
Place pie pan filled with water on lower rack in oven to keep cake moist while baking.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Wash, peel and slice cucumbers and onion. Blend other ingredients and pour over cucumbers and onions. Refrigerate before serving.

title: saimin
directions: In a large pot, bring water to a boil over high heat.
Add noodles and cook until tender, but firm, about 3 minutes.
Drain noodles and divide evenly between 4 large deep soup bowls. Garnish soup with slices of fish cake, pork and scallions, dividing these ingredients evenly between the bowls. Serve with soy sauce.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, eggs, flour, soda and cinnamon. Add to apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar mixed with lemon juice.

title: beauford stew
directions: Boil corn in 3 quarts of water in large pot for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add crab boil, salt, shrimp and sausage.
Cook for approximately 5 to 10 minutes (gently), until shrimp are done.
Can let it sit in pot for a few minutes until ready to serve, then drain it all and serve.

title: potato shell taco pie
directions: In saucepan
melt
butter or margarine.
Add milk and 2 tablespoons of
the
dry taco seasoning mix.
Remove from heat and stir in
potato flakes.
Press mixture over the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 10-inch pie plate.

title: rice pudding
directions: Eggs and cream should be at room temperature.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum Dutch oven (don't use iron pot as black iron pot will cause crawfish to darken).
Season crawfish tails generously with seasoning.
Add paprika to margarine.
Saute crawfish tails about 5 minutes.
Remove crawfish and set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in large chunks; cover with water and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut carrots, ham and celery into chunks; add to potatoes.
Also add onion and pepper to taste.
Boil until water is almost gone; fill pan with milk.
Cook about 20 to 30 more minutes.
This will thicken itself.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the chopped lettuce, tomatoes, onion and olives.
Brown the ground chuck and drain.
Add chili powder, garlic salt and pepper or the package of taco seasoning.
Allow to cool.

title: pink lemonade cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; cool completely.

title: pink yogurt dressing
directions: Beat with wire whip or in blender.
One quarter cup of water may be added if you like a thinner dressing.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for approximately 2 weeks.
Always shake well before serving.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in water to cover for 1/2 hour.
Squeeze juice from orange and add enough boiling water to make 1 cup.
Save skins.
Put drained apricots, cut up orange skins and raisins through a food chopper.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and beat in egg.
Add fruit and nuts.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange juice mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken devine
directions: Salt and pepper breasts.
In skillet, melt margarine and brown breasts on all sides.
Place browned breasts in greased casserole dish.
Add sour cream, sherry and cream of mushroom soup to the margarine in the skillet; mix well.
Pour the sauce over the breasts and cover the casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar gradually.
Add margarine, seasonings and flour a little at a time.
"You can bake right away or refrigerate overnight.
If you put in refrigerator, seasonings will go through batter.
The batter will be thin like cake batter."
Drop on iron and bake 30 to 40 seconds, about 1/2 teaspoon.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator up to 2 weeks, covered.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add rice, one spoon at a time.
Mix thoroughly after each spoonful until casserole is of desired consistency.
Cover with Italian bread crumbs (optional) and bake at 300° until done, about 1 hour.

title: rolled oats bread
directions: Mix cornmeal and hot water to form a thick batter.
Fry in greased skillet or bake in hot oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have both cheeses at room temperature.
Grate sharp cheese and mix together.
Roll into 3 fist size balls.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper and aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice carrots into rounds.
Boil peeled and sliced in salted water until soft; drain.
Mix cheese and butter with cooked carrots.
Pour in a shallow baking dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Spread in a greased and floured pan. Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand. Pour in pineapple and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Top with coconut. If desired, you can also top with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries, diced. Just before serving, you can also drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar in large heavy saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda (this foams up a lot, so be sure you use a tall, heavy saucepan).
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Pour in a large roaster pan (greased).
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all wet ingredients well.
Then add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add 1 cup flour, orange juice and flavoring; beat well. Add remainder of flour.
Pour in large pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: In a medium Dutch oven, brown hamburger.
Rinse hamburger in a colander; drain and return to Dutch oven.
Add green pepper, onion and celery and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer to blend flavors.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 4 cups of very warm water.
Mix 9 cups of flour, salt and sugar thoroughly.
Make a "well" in middle of flour mixture, placing the Crisco in the well.
Mix flour and Crisco while gradually adding warm yeast water.
Add additional 2 cups of warm water (approximately) to mixture until dough reaches desired consistency.
Start kneading, adding remaining flour as needed.
A good consistency for dough is when it will spring back when you are kneading, and yet it is not too dry.
Knead dough 5 to 7 minutes.
Cover with bread cloth and set in a warm place. Allow to rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in large cookie pan and top with bacon bits or crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: applesauce bread pudding(serves 4)
directions: Spread toasted bread with butter or margarine and cut into quarters.
Place, buttered side up, in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones.
Mix salmon, potato, onion, cracker crumbs, egg and black pepper.
With a spoon, form a ball with the mixture and roll in cornmeal.
Form small patties and fry until golden brown.

title: fruit balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar.
Roll in balls and then roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: herb cheese spread
directions: Mix and chill for spread.
If used as a dip, add yogurt to soften.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg and melted margarine.
Place in 9-inch baking dish.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 400° until crust rises to top and browns.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add shortening and eggs. Mix for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan, which has been coated with shortening and dusted with flour.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours (75 minutes) until done. Not necessary to frost.
May dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: wasabi miso flank steak(cooking light)
directions: Marinate for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Grill and baste with reserved marinade.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir in the cheese; simmer gently.
Makes 16 cups.

title: raspberry filled gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries, stir until berries are thawed.
Add celery, apples and stir well. Pour half of mixture into mold and let set.

title: vicki's party cookies
directions: Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Press thumb into cookies, leaving an imprint.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
When cool, fill centers with different frostings or jellies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of parsley and 1/2 cup of pecans in which to roll the cheese ball.
Mix all other ingredients well and place in refrigerator to harden.
Mold into ball and roll in reserved parsley and nuts.
Serve surrounded by crisp crackers.
Ideal for large parties.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and form a small cake (pat between hands) and fry.
If batter appears too thick, add more water a little at a time.
This is served at the Kutztown Folk Festival.
Eat with butter or gravy.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: tropical fruit drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; puree until creamy.
Makes 2 non-alcoholic drinks, or add rum to taste.
Garnish with pineapple stick or fresh mint.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together Jell-O and boiling water and let jell. Add strawberries to Jell-O mixture. Break up cake into a 9 x 13 pan. Pour the Jell-O mixture on slowly and let set. Better made the day before. Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses and beat well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients and add to the shortening mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate the dough for 1 hour.
Shape the dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball into sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
These cookies have crackled tops and sugar imparts a slight glaze.

title: lemon-glazed nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix and sugar.
Blend in eggs, oil and apricot nectar; beat 6 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 50 minutes.
Cool on cake rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan onto a cake rack; place cake rack on waxed paper.
Pour Lemon Glaze over hot cake, allowing icing to drizzle down sides.

title: neiman-marcus brownie
directions: Mix cake mix, nuts, 1 egg and melted butter together.
Spread on greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs together.
Pour on top of the cake.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the egg white and spread it over the crust; bake for five minutes at 375°.
Let the crust cool.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix together the butter and fresh garlic.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Butter insides of each half with butter mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Rub outside of bread with olive oil; wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Also good with Mozzarella cheese.

title: ritzy pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add 1 cup sugar or little less.
Fold in pecans, crackers and vanilla.
Place in slightly greased, 9-inch pie plate with sides slightly higher than center.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: field peas mexicana
directions: Crumble sausage into a heavy skillet.
Brown and drain.
Stir in onion and garlic; saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer mixture 60 to 90 minutes, stirring as needed.
Add a little more water during cooking if needed. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chocolate bars
directions: In 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan, melt oleo while heating oven to 350°.
Sprinkle and pat dry cake mix over oleo. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips, cherries and pecans. Drizzle condensed milk over the top.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Yield: about 1 1/2 cups or 14 ounces.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Break bread in pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Place in well-greased pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes and uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Place in mixer bowl in order listed above.
Beat low for 1 minute.
Scrape sides.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant; cut into small pieces.
Heat butter in skillet. Add onions and pepper.
Cook for a few minutes; add tomatoes, eggplant and seasoning. Cook for 10 minutes.
Place in shallow greased baking dish.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, until crumbs are browned.

title: lime punch
directions: Ice mold is made from lemonade, lemon slices and maraschino cherries.
Use both red and green to add color.

title: carrot salad (marinated)
directions: Refrigerate and marinate for 2 days.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2 inch thick.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat
tomato slices with mixture.
Heat shortening in skillet until sizzling hot.
Add tomatoes.
Cook quickly until brown
on
one
side.
Turn
tomatoes carefully.
Reduce heat. Cook until heated through.

title: meat ball stroganoff
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Form into meat balls and simmer until done.
Pour over mushroom and cream mixture and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs and bananas and beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Put soda in sour milk.
Alternate flour mixture and milk mixture, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until a straw comes out clean from the center.
Frost with whipped cream or any beaten fluffy white frosting.

title: o-deer
directions: Boil jumbo onions until soft enough to separate and make onion shells.
Brown the venison in a skillet in oil; combine the venison and remaining ingredients (except hoop cheese).
Try covering for half the time.

title: oyster stew
directions: In saucepan, cook oysters, water and salt until mixture boils. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes. Serve hot with saltine crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: After you make your tomato juice (makes about 8 quarts), mix everything together and heat to a boil and let simmer 1 hour.
Seal in jars.
Makes about 11 to 12 quarts.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pack mixture into a 2-quart glass baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook in microwave oven for 5 minutes at Medium-high setting.
Top with catsup; return to oven and rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes at High setting, or until done.
Remove from oven.
Cover with aluminum foil; let stand 5 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Place dip in hollowed out sourdough bread or pumpernickel bread to serve.
Use another loaf of it to cut into cubes to dip.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine 2 cups of the flour, 1/2 cup of sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press one half into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Now combine apples, remaining sugar, flour and cinnamon. Arrange on bottom crust.
Sprinkle any remaining crumbs over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crazy crescent lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add onion, bell peppers and seasoning to meat.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Mix eggs and 3 cheeses together.
Pour tomato sauce in mixture.
Pour layer of hamburger mixture, then layer of cheese mixture, then hamburger and so on.
Make last layer cheese.
Fold the ends of the rolls to the middle.
Put a little milk on top to seal. Top with sesame seed, if desired.
Bake at 350°
until brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into muffin pans lined with muffin papers and freeze.

title: layer salad
directions: Put peas in warm (not too hot) water until thawed; drain good. Mix vegetables together.
Add sugar and mayonnaise together, then spread on the vegetables.
Add cheese and bacon bits.

title: bambini
directions: Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses in a small bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Halve each biscuit horizontally, forming 20 thin biscuits.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat until clear and remove from heat.
Add a few drops of red food coloring and 4 tablespoons strawberry jello dry powder.
Stir well.
Fill pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Pour cooked filling over berries.
Place in refrigerator and chill until thick.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: line shack chili
directions: Brown cubed beef in greased or oiled frying pan over steady heat.
Drain off all fat.
Put meat into chili pot with onion, garlic, green chiles and chicken broth.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; stir, then reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender, 2 hours or more.
Serves 12.

title: wassail
directions: Put all ingredients into large pot and simmer for about 2 hours.
Serve hot or cold with a cinnamon stick in each cup.

title: chocolate nut toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat remaining margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add flour and cocoa; mix well.
With floured hands, press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: mom's eggnog
directions: In blender, mix the egg yolks, 4 teaspoons sugar and milk. Add nutmeg to taste.
In medium bowl with hand mixer, beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar to make stiff meringue. Add more sugar, if needed.
Pour the blender mixture into 4 glasses and add egg white mixture and extra nutmeg.

title: caramel icing
directions: Stir sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Melt 1/2 cup sugar; while hot, stir melted sugar in milk and sugar while both are boiling.
Stir in margarine.
Cook to a soft ball stage (drop some drops of icing into a small bowl with cold water to test it). This is enough to icing a 2 layer cake.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: chinese chicken and vegetables
directions: Heat oil, over medium-high heat, in a large frypan or wok. Stir-fry chicken chunks, ginger and garlic for 2 to 3 minutes. Add vegetables and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry until heated through.
Add chicken broth.
Heat.
Mix cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce together; stir into hot mixture.
Heat to boiling and sauce is thickened.
Serve with steamed rice or fried rice.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add spinach.
Melt butter and cook onion and mushrooms.
Add with tarragon to spinach mixture. Salt to taste.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: crabbies
directions: Split muffins.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread on muffin halves.
Freeze overnight.
Broil until light brown.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: pimento
directions: Wash whole peppers.
Place in oven 6 to 8 minutes to loosen skin.
Dip quickly in cold water, then peel and cut up.
Place in jars and flatten.
Add salt.
Put jars in pressure cooker and process 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.
Add no liquid to jars.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine sugar and water in
heavy pan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and add peanuts.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until mix is dry and peanuts are cooked with sugar.
Place in flat pan and bake in 250° oven about 1 1/2 hours, checking every 30 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: homemade clam chowder
directions: Mix
the water, the onions, the celery, the carrots and the potatoes;
boil
for 1/2 hour or until the vegetables are done. Add the clams, including the juice.
Heat the milk to a boil and add
to
the clam mixture.
Heat the cooking oil and mix with the flour.
Add gradually to the clam mixture and let boil slowly over a
low
fire, stirring and mixing well.
Heat to a boiling point and
reduce
the heat.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until
the soup
is
slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Put out fire
and serve.
Serves
Winter days delight of a nourishment.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk, adding a small amount of food coloring to it.
Just enough to turn it pink.

title: grandmother's white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into very warm water; stir in 1/2 teaspoon of the sugar.
Stir until dissolved and let double in volume. Combine remaining sugar, milk, margarine and salt; heat just until margarine melts.
Pour into a large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, adding flour as needed.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn to bring greased side up.
Cover and set in a warm, draft free place to rise to double in bulk.
Punch down.
Knead a few times, cut in half.
Let rest, covered, for 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves. Place in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Cover and let rise again. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until loaves are lightly browned and sound hollow when tapped.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Cook raisins in the water until tender.
Add sugar and cornstarch, then add butter, syrup and vinegar.
Cook until thick and then add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together and mix in chopped pecans; set aside.
Beats eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and raisins.
Add dry ingredients and stir only until ingredients are moist.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.

title: potato and bacon frittata
directions: In an 8-inch nonstick skillet, that has an oven-safe or removable handle, heat oil and margarine together until margarine is melted.

Remove from heat. Spread potato slices in single layer over bottom and 1-inch up sides of skillet. Top with onion slices and any remaining potato slices. Set another 8-inch skillet, bottom side down, over potato and onion to weight them down and cook over medium heat until potato slices are tender, about 10 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 450°.

title: meatball subs
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.

title: jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O in a 9 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch glass loaf pan.
Stir well until dissolved.
Pour pineapple and orange juice into 1 cup measuring cup; add ice cubes to make full cup.
Stir juice mix into Jell-O mix until ice is melted.
Add carrots, pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate 4 hours until set.
Unmold; place on lettuce leaves.
To serve, slice like a cake.

title: sausage and noodles
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Brown in large pan. While browning, start water to cook noodles.
When sausage is browned, add onion, green pepper, olive oil and garlic.
(Onion and pepper should be cut into approximately 1-inch pieces.) Continue cooking sausage mixture like stir-fry until noodles are done.
Drain noodles and toss into sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serve immediately.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in uncooked pie shell. Cover with the other uncooked pie shell.
Pierce top shell with fork a few times.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: lite lasagna
directions: About 2 hours before serving, prepare lasagna noodles as label directs; drain.
In medium bowl, with fork, mash tofu; stir in Romano cheese, parsley, salt, egg and cottage cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In 3-quart shallow casserole, arrange half of noodles.
Spread half of tofu mixture over noodles.
Arrange half zucchini.
Sprinkle with half Mozzarella.
Top with half spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Bake 40 minutes or until heated through.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes for easier serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in corn, egg, cheese and corn bread mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet snack
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix Rice Krispies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Pour over mixture in pan.

title: reese's cup cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape in 1-inch balls.
Put into small muffin tins and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 370°.
Take out of oven and insert miniature Reese's cup until just the top shows. Cool in tins about 10 minutes and remove.
Makes 48.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth; fold in Cool Whip.
Set aside.

title: no eggs chocolate cake (moist)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well; pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or test to see if it is done.
Use your favorite icing.

title: roasting whole tenderloin
directions: Allow to marinate 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Roast the meat for 7 minutes per pound for rare, 10 minutes per pound for medium.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna potato chip casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange in alternate layers.
Finish with a sprinkling of potato chip crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: ham or salami party roll-up finger food
directions: I used horseradish to make a cheese spread. You may need a little milk to make the cream cheese to spread easier.
Spread a slice of meat with a little cream cheese mixture.
Roll up and use scissors and cut each end to be smooth and in an angel, then cut in half in an angle. Continue in this manner until meat is used up.

title: turtles
directions: Put 1 can of sweetened condensed milk (unopened) into a deep pan of boiling water.
Cook for two hours, making sure that it stays covered by the water (can cook up to three cans at a time). Cool at least two hours.
Open your can and you have caramel. (Can cook ahead and store in unopened can.)

title: congo cookie bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar. Cool. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, salt and baking powder. Add nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 225° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Dump all ingredients into large skillet except rice and eggs. Stir over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until heated through thoroughly.
Add scrambled eggs and cooked rice; stir just to heat through.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix until creamy the first 4 items. Fill cupcake tins with Nilla wafers.
Place 1 tablespoon of cheese mix on top of wafer. Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Top with any fruit or leave plain.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease (not oil) popover pans or muffin pans.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
Add remaining ingredients and beat just enough until blended.
Fill greased cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes until deep golden brown.
Prick crust with top of knife during last 5 minutes to let steam escape.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 or 7 large popovers.

title: pound cake (moist)
directions: Cream butter, Crisco
and
sugar;
add	eggs,
one at a time. Mix in half flour and half milk; add remaining milk and flour with vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Remove paper from boxes of spinach. Microwave as per directions. Drain well. Fry bacon with chopped onion for 10 minutes. Crumble bacon. Add flour and salt, blending well. Slowly stir in milk a little at a time. Cook and stir until thickened. Fold in the spinach. Sprinkle bacon over all.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in water until tender.
Add other ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, uncovered for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cucumber salad dressing pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Let stand overnight in brine made with 1/2 cup salt to 3 quarts water.
Next day, slice thin or chop onions.
Mix sugar and spices with flour and vinegar.
Add drained cucumbers, onions and pimento.
Cook, uncovered.
Turn down heat, stir and cook 10 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour, cocoa and soda.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: emily's fudge
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar, syrup, chocolate and evaporated milk. Cook to soft ball stage.
Take off heat; add butter and vanilla without stirring.
Let stand until you can hold the bottom of the pan comfortably.
(Leave wooden spoon in the pan.)
Beat with electric beaters.
When it stops looking waxy, take the beaters out and beat by hand.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that's been buttered.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: crisp oatmeal quicks
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in beaten eggs.
Gradually blend in mixture of flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold in oatmeal, then cornflakes and vanilla.
Add one of the choice ingredients.
Blend choice in well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: empty cupboard casserole
directions: Heat to boiling green beans and potatoes with garlic and salt. Simmer for a couple of minutes. Drain. Wash squash and slice.
Cook with onion, salt and butter until tender. Drain. Layer in small Pyrex dish.
Top with cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Cut the broccoli flowers into bite size pieces.
Slice the stalk part into thin slices. The lower part may need to be peeled before slicing.
Combine the bacon, chopped onion, raisins, sunflower seeds and prepared broccoli.
Combine the mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and mix well with other ingredients.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spud and spice cake
directions: Combine sugar, mashed potatoes, shortening, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in large mixing bowl.
Cream thoroughly, about 4 minutes.
Add eggs; mix until thoroughly blended.
Combine soda and buttermilk or sour milk.
Add alternately with sifted flour to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Coat chopped walnuts with 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir into batter.
Turn into
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, well greased and lightly floured on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost. Makes one 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: eggs yummy
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter, then crumble hamburg buns into pan.
Sprinkle cheese over buns.
In a large bowl, beat 6 eggs with 2 cups of milk until well blended.
Pour over buns.

title: ice cream salad
directions: *Use juice drained from crushed pineapple.
Add water, if needed, to make 1 cup.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix well. Alternate filling, cookies and bananas until all is used. Top with cookies. Makes a bunch.

title: layered salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp (less than 1 pound can be used, if desired); drain and crumble.
Whip mayonnaise with sugar.
Shred lettuce; layer in large dish with celery, onion, peas, cheese, bacon and mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of pork shops.
Roll in flour and brown in a skillet.
Place in casserole dish and cover with chicken gumbo soup.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 2 hours.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: ooey-gooey cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Consistency should be like cookie dough.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into pan, making the top layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Chop pepperoni.
Mix all ingredients together spreading pepperoni as you add it.
Put into greased 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 45 minutes.
Let cool for 15 - 20 minutes and cut into squares.
Serve warm or cold as an appetizer.

title: mediterranean lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna per package directions.
In a large skillet, brown sausage meat and ground beef.
Drain. Add Ricotta, half of the Mozzarella, Parmesan, garlic, Italian seasoning, wine, pepper, onion, salt and pepper to taste and tomato paste.

title: nutty cheese gems
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Chill until firm. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Coat balls with pistachio nuts.
Chill in a single layer until firm.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: french spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Drain well, approximately 1/2 hour.
In large skillet put 2 to 4 tablespoons oil.
Add 4 to 6 cloves garlic.
Heat to point garlic is completely mixed with oil. Pour spaghetti into skillet.
Toss well.
Pour onto platter; pour topping over.
Serve hot!

title: old fashioned apple pie(that you always thought mother made.)
directions: Pare and slice apples. Sift flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon together.
Mix with apples.

Line pie pan with pastry. Fill with apple mixture and dot with butter. Cover with top crust and slash crust in several places. Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to moderate oven (350°) and bake for 45 more minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: waffles #1
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and vegetable oil and cook in waffle iron.

title: icebox biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water with 1 tablespoon of the sugar.
Sift together flour, remaining sugar and cream of tartar.
Add cool melted Crisco and buttermilk to flour mixture. Let rise 1 hour.
Place in the refrigerator.
About 1 hour before baking time, remove as much dough as you will use.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Butter tops and let stand at room temperature and rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 325°.
This mixture can be kept for several days.

title: grated carrot salad
directions: Mix grated carrots, chopped ginger, lemon juice, salt and spices; set aside.
Heat oil.
When hot, add green chilies and mustard seed.
When the seed starts making a cracking sound, remove from heat and pour over the salad mixture.
Mix well; garnish with cilantro.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix well together.
Put in small muffin pan.
Bake at 325° for about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift the next 4 ingredients.
Add the oats, raisins, nuts and milk.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with foil liners.
Place wafers in each liner.
Mix cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool and chill. Top with pie filling (cherry or strawberry) or top with nuts.

title: boiled ham
directions: Stir beer and molasses into water until dissolved, in large, 6 to 8-quart pot.
Add ham and simmer on stove, uncovered, over very low heat for 2 hours.

title: cornflake ice cream dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well and carefully until all flakes are chocolate covered.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Let cool and become firm in refrigerator.
Take out and add vanilla ice cream on top.
May sprinkle with chocolate chips, optional.

title: vatzian vegetarian delight
directions: Toast bagel; take tomato, lettuce and pickle spears and place on the toasted bagel.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Viola!

title: dried fruitcake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cover; let marinate at room temperature for several hours or overnight.
Stir 1 or 2 times.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients,
simmer 10 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Serve hot with melba rounds.

title: chris' favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo; combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Dip tops in sugar and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Press down with glass bottom.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes about 100.

title: strawberry delights
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with Cool Whip in a large bowl until stiff. Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Chill and serve.

title: betty ann's 60-elephant fudge, hot fudge or icing
directions: Mix the
sugar, cocoa and salt; add Karo, milk and oleo and mix
well.	Stir over low heat until oleo melts, then stir constantly to
full
boil over high heat.
At full boil, count to 60	elephants (1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Ready now
to
use as hot fudge over ice cream.
Beat a little to use as	cake
icing.
Beat
a
little
(well,
more than a little) more
to
make
fudge.
One cup of pecans may be added before spreading on buttered pan.	When set, cut into squares.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add remaining ingredients with 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: caramel delights
directions: Bring sugar, Pet milk and butter to boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except reserved 1/4 cup butter and bread crumbs; pour mixture into well greased casserole (or 13 x 9-inch baking dish). Sprinkle top with crumbs and 1/4 cup butter. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: creamed ham and artichokes
directions: Cook artichokes and drain well.
Combine soup, onion, sherry, salt and pepper.
Arrange artichokes, ham and eggs in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add soup mix.
Add garlic salt and cover with cheese for last 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bill's awesome apple crispies
directions: You will need a knife, spoon and patience, large bowl and greased baking pan.

title: mixed vegetables italienne
directions: Put all ingredients in a 10-inch skillet (young zucchini need not be peeled).
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream-filled cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fill 24 paper lined muffin cups (2 1/2 inches in diameter) 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Prepare Vanilla Cream.
Spoon into pastry tube with open star tip.
Insert tip into center of top of cupcake.
Squeeze gently until cupcake begins to peak.
Cover top with swirl of Filling (Or cut a 1 1/2-inch cone from top of cupcake.
Fill; replace cone.
Swirl filling over top.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening into bananas with sugar.
Blend in egg.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Put into greased loaf pan (paper lined).
Put into cold oven, set at 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes without opening oven.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (until firm).
Mix sour cream, vanilla, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour over baked mixture and bake for 5 minutes.
If you want to top the cheesecake with fruit, omit the cinnamon.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg and sour milk. Mix dry ingredients together and add to shortening mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icing
directions: When cake has baked 18 minutes, combine margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and add remaining ingredients. Pour over cake as soon as you take it from oven.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: frank barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients over low heat for 30 minutes.
Throw franks in sauce.

title: old settler's butter beans
directions: Brown together the bacon, beef and onion.
Pour off drippings. Mix butter beans, kidney beans, pork and beans, brown and white sugars, ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire and molasses.
Add to the bacon, beef and onion.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Easily serves 10 people.

title: pineapple nut pies
directions: Mix
Eagle
Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple
and
pecans.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken olive casserole
directions: Saute chicken and chopped onion in 2 tablespoons peanut oil. Cook and drain noodles.
Mix together chicken, noodles, soup, milk and olives in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: picadillo
directions: Cook meat and celery in large pan until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes, covered. Serve over rice or buns.

title: apple cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heap apples into pie shell.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar and cinnamon (reserve a little for top). Beat cream and eggs together.
Pour over the apples.
Spread Jack cheese on top. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes, then serve.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a skillet.
Drain off grease. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been greased, layer meat and onion mixture, then layer the rice, carrots, potatoes and celery. Dilute mushroom soup with 1 1/2 cans of water.
Mix well and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until vegetables are cooked through.

title: topsy turvy
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl and serve.
Quick and easy for the kids.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon in hand-cranked freezer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch pieces.
Put in boiling chicken broth.
Cook until done.
Add chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pink passion dessert
directions: In mixer, mix together milk and Cool Whip.
Fold in pie filling and drained pineapple.
Chill for a few hours.

title: crock-pot chicken brunswick stew
directions: The night before serving, put potatoes, onion, tomatoes and cut up chicken in the crock-pot.
Cook on low overnight.
Next morning, take chicken out.
Remove skin and bones, then tear chicken into small pieces and return to crock-pot.
Stir in sauces and catsup.
Cook on low until one hour before dinner.
Add corn, stir well and leave on low until ready to serve.

title: twinkie torte
directions: Melt chocolate bits, water and sugar.
Cool.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture and fold in cream.
Cut Twinkies into thirds, lengthwise.
Arrange on bottom of 8-inch torte pan.
Add half of chocolate mixture.
Add other half of Twinkies.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: While broccoli is thawing in 1 cup boiling water and rice is cooking, saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup and milk. Simmer for 3 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Add seasonings.
Pour into Pam-sprayed casserole and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in glass container.
Cook on High power for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in margarine and vanilla and cook for 1 minute longer.
Add baking soda and stir well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet; let cool and break into pieces.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop together tomatoes, apples, onions and peppers.
Add salt and water.
Soak for 1 hour.
Pour in colander and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and pickling spices with tomatoes, apples, onions and peppers.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal!

title: mock turkey
directions: Mix together and place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese style hamburger hash
directions: Brown meat in hot oil until crumbly.
Add chopped onion, celery and soups.
Rinse out cans with the warm water and add to mixture.
Stir in uncooked rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Turn into a large lightly greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes; remove cover and continue baking for 30 minutes longer. Cover the mixture with the noodles and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in 1-quart casserole. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Serve hot with toasted bread slices or tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole and cover.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: m&m cheesecake bars
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture.
Press rest into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: cookie's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together. Add sugar. Add eggs 2 at a time. Add all flavors together. Add flour slowly. Mix all ingredients on medium speed for 3 to 4 minutes. Bake in a 16 x 4 loaf baking pan for 1 hour at 300°. Be sure to flour and grease pan.

title: fruit soup
directions: Soak pearl tapioca in 2 cups water overnight.
Drain and slice fruits.
Cook juice and tapioca about 1 hour until it looks clear, stirring often.
Add red hots to juice, stir until dissolved.
Add dried currants to hot juice, then add all to cool fruit.
Keep in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: jello easter dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes, until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping with whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours, or until firm.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust (1)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Dough should be real smooth and elastic or stiff.
Roll out on a floured surface.

title: stir-fry pork
directions: To love and honor are okay,

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix juices and water to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add Cherry Jello (mix).
Add cold water.
Mix blueberries and pineapple and add to Jello mixture.
Refrigerate over night.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Add oats, baking powder, salt and milk.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake
as directed.	Bake half of the batter at 350° for 15 minutes.
In
a saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with butter and milk.
Remove cake from	oven and pour caramel mixture over cake.	Sprinkle with chocolate
chips	and
nuts. Pour second half of batter over top and
return to oven.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done.

title: kevin's kwik pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on top of hamburger bun.
Top with pepperoni slices or any other topping you desire.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated oven until cheese is melted and oozing off, 10 to 12 minutes.
Pull out of oven and enjoy.

title: tessie smith's orange chiffon cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in angel food or Bundt pan.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix well and cover with topping.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Make layers of bread and cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 to 24 hours.
Better if it stands at least overnight.
Place dish in pan of hot water in oven.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Cook for about 10 minutes; let cool.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate in 2 cups of milk on low heat and set aside. Mix sugar and flour; add 1/2 cup of milk and mix thoroughly.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to thicken.
Add beaten egg yolks and margarine.
Cook until thick and creamy.
(A double boiler can be used.)
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: light and tasty baked chicken
directions: Combine dry milk powder, poultry seasoning, dry mustard, parsley flakes, paprika, instant bouillon, salt and pepper in bowl.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Roll in seasoning mixture, coating well.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Yield:
4 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Press dough into 10-inch pie plate to form crust.
Spread with mustard.
Saute zucchini and onion in margarine in skillet until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least two hours before serving.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 1/2 stick (4 tablespoons) butter.
Melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of cake pan (9-inch round x 3-inch deep).
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentric circles.
In a small bowl, beat remaining 1 1/2 sticks butter with sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg yolks. Alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla until well blended.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to stiffness.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Spread over peach slices.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until cake tester comes out dry.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Turn cake onto plate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat 1/3 cup margarine with soup and sour cream.
Add chopped onions and grated cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: rice with browned onions
directions: Measure, wash and soak rice in cold water until needed.
Chop onions into small pieces or slice lengthwise into thin sections. Use a 6-quart aluminum pot.
Add oil and chopped onion.
Saute and stir until onion just begins to brown.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer so brown color will spread throughout.
Cook about 2 minutes until boiling.
Add rice and stir.
Add water (2 cups for each cup of rice).
Stir and add salt.
Cover and simmer on low, stirring occasionally.
Makes enough rice for about 8 people.

title: beef and mushrooms
directions: Cut sirloin into thin strips about 4-inch long. In a large fry pan brown meat in oil. Add onion and garlic powder. Cook until onions are tender. Add soy sauce, mushrooms, beef bouillon cubes and 2 cups water. Cover and simmer until meat is tender 30 to 40 minutes. Combine cornstarch with remaining 1/2 cup water and add to meat mixture. Additional water can be added if sauce is too thick. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Serve over hot fluffy rice or noodles. Tip: if desired 1/2 cup drained and sliced water chestnuts or 1/2 package (7 ounce) frozen snow pea pods can be added.

title: chilean salad
directions: Cut onion in very thin slices vertically.
"Wash" the onion in cold water for several minutes, firmly squeezing the onion to get out all strong taste.
Rinse and drain well.
Peel tomatoes; cut in thin slices vertically.
Season with salad oil and cilantro. Good!

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well, then add chocolate chips last.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, butter, milk, salt and vanilla, beating until well mixed.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown pork sausage, drain off some of fat.
Pour savoy dressing mix in skillet, add onion (white and green), bell pepper and celery and simmer until seasoning is soft.
Add dressing mix and sausage to rice and mix.
Season to taste with Tony's and Accent.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for coloring.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Of Mexican and Indian origin, Sopaipillas are presented as the very first course in New Mexican restaurants that feature traditional Spanish or Mexican food.
When the small pieces of dough are cooked in hot oil, they puff out and form bread with a crisp crust and hollow center.
They are served hot, coated with honey or rolled in cinnamon sugar.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of each ingredient at a time, creating 8 layers.
End with the whipped topping.
Garnish with Heath bits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Butter casserole.
Stir altogether (except onion rings).
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, onions, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup condensed tomato soup.
Mix thoroughly; shape in about 20 small balls and brown on cookie sheet in oven.
Drain balls on paper towels.

title: carne empanada
directions: Wash meat and cut into strips.
Beat meat to tenderize. Combine cloves of garlic and pepper.
Marinate the meat with these ingredients.
Chill meat in refrigerator for a while.

title: autumn apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, margarine (oil) and vanilla.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add floured apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: susie's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and peanut butter.
Roll into balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from stove and add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter. Blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or aluminum foil. Sets up quickly.

title: 9-minute peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook 4 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend. Microwave again for 30 seconds on High.
Add soda and gently stir until well mixed.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet (do not scrape bowl).
Cool 1/2 hour.
Break into pieces to serve.

title: crisp lemon cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Form into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove from sheet.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with melted margarine and brown sugar.
Divide this mixture into 2 equal parts.
Put half of the crumbs into the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 3-inch dish.
Reserve the rest.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
