In another bowl, whip cold evaporated milk until thick with electric mixer.
Gradually add white sugar and vanilla.
Add the jello mixture and beat well.
Pour the jello mixture onto crumbs.
Add the remaining crumbs on top of the jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: no-punch punch
directions: Add 1 tray ice cubes.
Put in icebox.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Pour eggs, sugar and shortening over bread cubes and pineapple.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender (15 minutes); set aside.
Cook chicken and season to taste.
Take chicken off bone.
In casserole, place layer of broccoli, then layer of chicken.
Mix soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese until covered, then sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring oleo, brown sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir vigorously and spoon over 2 bags of hull-less popcorn.
A roasting pan works well enough.
Mix well to coat.
Bake in 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every fifteen minutes.
Break apart and store.

title: zesty winter vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook carrots in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
Add Brussels sprouts and continue cooking for 10 minutes more or until crisp-tender. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Place vegetables and reserved liquid in 1 1/2-quart baking dish or casserole; toss lightly to combine.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk; mix well.
Pour this batter into baking dish over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Over the batter spoon 3 cups fruit.
Again, do not mix!
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over fruit.
Sprinkle spices over fruit.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 8-quart Dutch oven; fill with water until chicken is covered.
Add parsley, oregano, Italian seasoning, garlic, salt and pepper.
Take chicken out to cool when fully cooked.
To the broth, add soups and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cut up biscuits and put in boiling broth.
Debone chicken and add to dumplings and broth.
Be sure to stir every few minutes for duration of cooking to prevent sticking and burning. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: neiman marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Blend together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chocolate chips, candy and nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bring to a boil the milk and butter.
In separate bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, chocolate, egg yolks and enough milk to make moist.
When milk mixture boils, add dry ingredients and stir.
When thick, pour in vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in large bowl.
Add all rest of ingredients.
Mix well and bake in shallow dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super chili
directions: Boil pinto beans until tender, about 3 to 4 hours.
Make sure when they are done, there is about 3 to 4 cups of juice in them. Dice up onion and add it to ground beef.
Brown this in skillet. Drain off fat and add to pinto beans.
Add honey, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about an hour.
Top with grated American cheese.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine soup, cottage cheese and milk in saucepan.
Heat to melt soup.
Add cubed Cheddar cheese.
Cook macaroni and drain. Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Sift the self-rising flour, yeast and sugar.
Pour liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients.
Stir and store until ready to bake; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Bake at 400° to 425° in greased muffin tins for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked stuffed mushroom marsala
directions: Leave mushroom caps whole.
Chop stems.
Heat 6 tablespoons butter with oil.
Add garlic and onion.
Saute until onion is wilted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, parsley, lemon juice, tarragon and chopped mushroom stems.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak lima beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Next morning, throw out water, put fresh water in pot (enough to cover) and cook until tender (not mushy).
Saute bacon and onion.
Save a little sugar and a few bacon pieces for top.
Save about 1/2 cup cooking water to use when combining cooked beans, fried bacon and onion.
Add soup.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Put in baking dish. Top with brown sugar and bacon pieces or strips.
Bake at 350° until brown on top (about 1 hour).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into pieces (enough to line bottom of baking dish).
Line bottom of baking dish with cabbage, then layer remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until cabbage seems done.

title: quiche
directions: Saute onion, garlic and optional vegetables in butter.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Add cheeses.
Add vegetables and/or meat. Stir together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pauline brandls' punch
directions: Boil water, dissolve sugar into water, cool, add remaining ingredients except for the gingerale. Refrigerate.
At serving time, add fresh gingerale for fizz. Serves 60 to 75 people. Very refreshing.

title: special k or corn flakes bars
directions: Bring sugar and white syrup to a boil.
(Do not boil.) Take from fire and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Special K or cornflakes.
Spread in buttered dish.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into bars.

title: mushroom crust quiche
directions: In a frying pan, melt 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add mushrooms and cook until limp.
Stir in crushed crackers.
Turn mixture into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Press mixture evenly over pan bottom and up sides.

title: dennis' favorite health drink
directions: In a blender container, combine orange sherbet, orange juice, ice cubes and pink grapefruit juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses halfway full and add remaining seltzer water.
Stir.
Serves 6.
Kids love this drink!

title: winter vegetable stew
directions: In a medium sauce pot over a moderate heat, saute garlic and mushrooms in the olive oil for 2-3 minutes.
Add in zucchini and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Saute for another 5 minutes. Add in chick peas, cumin, tomatoes, an rosemary.
Bring this to a stew to bubble, reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Wash, peel and cut oranges into thin slices.
Chop pineapple into small chunks.
Slice bananas.
Combine fruit and stir in powdered sugar and shredded coconut.
Sprinkle some coconut on top.
Chill.
Serve in small individual bowls or large bowl. Garnish with cherries or strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot layer cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil together.
Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth. Add chopped pecans and grated carrots.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layer pans at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cornish hens
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, peel, salt and cinnamon.
Add bread cubes.
Sprinkle with half the melted butter or margarine and the 4 teaspoons of orange juice.
Toss to mix.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse with cold water and drain well.
Combine macaroni and next 3 ingredients; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and pickle juice; mix well.
Pour over macaroni mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges.

title: ultimate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine brownie mix, eggs, oil, water, pudding mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips, stirring just until chips are mixed in.
Bake in buttered 9 x 11-inch baking pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini or yellow squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by teaspoon into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: banana chocolate bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in vanilla and egg. Blend in bananas and then flour mixture. Stir in chocolate pieces.
Spread in greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Cut into 30 bars.
Store tightly covered.

title: cheese salad
directions: Grate all the ingredients and then mix with mayonnaise just enough to hold together.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and milk together.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and butter.
Pour in creamed corn.
Bake in oblong cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in boiler.
Bring to a boil and then turn down and let simmer over low fire for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Combine with onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with enough cracker crumbs to make a topping.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: meatballs gingerly spiced
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Form into 30 meatballs.
In large saucepan combine ketchup and soda.
Heat to boiling and add raw meatballs.
Simmer 45 minutes, uncovered, until meat is cooked and sauce is thickened.
Serve over hot buttered rice or noodles.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: Layer peppers, alternately with cheese in a deep buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix beaten eggs, butter, salt, pepper and cumin.
Pour mixture over the peppers and cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This spicy souffle-like dish serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chocolate chip cookies (1)
directions: Mix above ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small to medium mixing bowl. Beat with mixer on low or with whisk until smooth.
Serve over fresh fruit salad.
Add to individual servings or add to a larger bowl of prepared fruits.

title: danish apple pudding
directions: Combine finely crushed zwieback bars with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon applesauce into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with crumb mixture.
Cook slowly on a low heat.
Serve warm and spoon whipped cream over pudding.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and packed brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Finally, fold in the gumdrops and chill batter for one hour.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart on a well greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in oven set at 400°.
This recipe makes about 5 dozen cookies.
Can be frozen to serve later.
A real favorite of children.

title: frozen fruit salad delicious
directions: Mix together whipped cream, sour cream, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Blend in walnuts, cherries and pineapple.
Peel and dice banana.
Fold in.
Spoon into 12 muffin papers and leave in muffin tin.
Place in freezer and leave there until firm.
Makes 12 individual servings.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Blend melted butter and flour.
Add milk gradually and cook until smooth and thickened.
Add seasonings and onion.
Simmer until onion is soft.
Add tuna and peas and mix thoroughly.
Serve over toast or English muffins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Tip: Measure first 3 ingredients and have them ready before you remove from fire.

title: easy coconut frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla. Cook over medium heat for 12 minutes, until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add coconut. Beat until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash and cook the potatoes without paring.
Mix all ingredients well, taking care they do not lose their identity. Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel pillows
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets with butter Crisco. Cream 1/2 cup butter Crisco, cream cheese and milk in medium bowl at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Beat in brown sugar.
Beat in 1/2 cup preserves.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Drop 2 level measuring tablespoons of dough into a mound to form each cookie.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: peanut kiss cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugars; then add egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 36 balls, roll balls in brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven, press Hershey Kiss on top of each cookie so that cookie cracks.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Yields 36 delicious peanut kiss cookies.

title: lamb or beef with yoghurt(lebanese dish)
directions: Boil the lamb or beef in water and salt for 30 minutes.
Add onions and cook until the meat is well done.
There will be very little broth left.
Add Yoghurt Sauce to meat and onions; cook over low flame for 15 to 20 minutes, until it thickens.
Brown garlic and mint in butter and add to the yoghurt and meat.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In separate bowl, mix all dressing ingredients together and chill.
Right before serving, add almonds and oranges and toss with dressing.

title: barbecue beef ribs(microwave)
directions: Wipe ribs with damp paper towels.
Place in microwave dish. Add 1/2 cup water and 1 sliced onion.

title: skewered chicken thighs in cumin
directions: You will also need 15 to 20 wooden skewers, soaked in water.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts. Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix well and add 1 cup of chocolate chips. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chips on top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits and dressing together in a large bowl.
You may add and/or substitute other fruits.
I sprinkle lemon juice on the apples before mixing them in the salad.
This keeps them from turning brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt butter; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda and flour.
Add bananas. Add nuts.
Save some of nuts to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: louise's holiday punch
directions: Add all ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil, then simmer 30 minutes, uncovered.
A good beverage and also nice holiday fragrance.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Remove skin and bone; cut into small pieces into a buttered casserole.
Mix together cream of celery soup, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Spread over cut up chicken.
Spread dressing crumbs (use dry, out of package) over soup mixture.
Drizzle with melted butter, gently, over crumbs. Use an 8 x 12-inch casserole or a little larger.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, Jell-O, water and cornstarch to a rolling boil and boil 3 minutes.
Cool and pour over sliced strawberries in a cooled, baked pie shell.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: ernie's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and beat well. Add mashed bananas, flour, baking soda and nuts. Pour into pans and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when center is tested.

title: charcoal beef
directions: Prepare large bed of completely white charcoal.
Roll wet roast in salt until completely coated.
Wrap coated roast in 7 sheets of waxed paper (each approximately 36-inches long).
Wrap in alternate directions, making sure that there are no open spots.
Place the covered roast directly on the coals; stand back and watch the flames engulf your $30.00 piece of beef.

Turn 1/3 after 20 minutes; repeat each 20 minutes for 60 minutes total cooking time. Remove from fire and scrape off any waxed paper ashes, the salt forms a crust which prevents the paper from sticking.
The roast will be medium rare, charcoal flavored and the best you ever had. This recipe will only work with an eye round cut, and coarsely flaked salt.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Debone and chop; reserve broth.
Cook onions in small amount of oil; add 2 cups of broth, salt, pepper, garlic powder and chicken.
Add chilies and soups; heat thoroughly.
Cut tortillas in quarters and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan, alternating them with chicken mixture, cheese and tortillas.
Repeat tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese 2 or 3 times with chicken on top.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: chestnut pea salad
directions: Layer in this order in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not stir.
Make it night before.
When serving, dip spoon down to bottom of dish.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn 5 minutes.
Cut from cob.
Measure.
Peel onions; remove seed from peppers.
Chop and measure cabbage, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients with 1 cup water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Bring to boiling.
Pack, boiling hot, into hot jars; seal at once.
Good served with peas, butter beans or other vegetables or meats.

title: kris kringles
directions: Mix together Karo syrup and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter; stir until well blended.
In a large bowl, mix the peanut butter mixture with the Rice Krispies. Stir to coat.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in a double boiler.
Frost the Rice Krispie mixture with the melted chips.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: deviled chicken thighs
directions: Put garlic through press.
Mince fresh ginger.
Combine both with soy, pepper and water.
Bring to boil in heavy pan large enough to hold chicken.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat.
Simmer in covered pan 10 minutes.
Remove cover.
Turn chicken pieces over and raise heat so liquid boils briskly.
Boil chicken 10 to 12 minutes until liquid evaporates and chicken turns a golden color. Serve with rice.
Remaining liquid is good over the rice.

title: eggless devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil, vanilla and vinegar.
Over all, pour cold water; mix well with spoon, but do not beat.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
If taking out of pans, cool for 10 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Mix all ingredients.
Roast for 2 hours. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: danish abelskivers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all of the ingredients but the egg whites; mix well.
Fold egg whites into the batter.
Heat Abelskivers pan until a drop of water will sizzle in it.
Put 1/2 teaspoon melted butter in each cup.
Fill each compartment 1/2 full.
Cook until lightly brown.
Turn dough once and cook other side.
Serve with maple syrup, butter, powdered sugar or jelly.

title: perky pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water until frosty.
Add pecans and coat well.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add nuts and mix. Bake in a jelly roll pan at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: holiday butternut squash
directions: Bake squash in microwave or oven; be sure to put an X (using a small knife) in each squash prior to baking to prevent exploding. Bake until squash is soft, but not mushy. Remove squash from shell and place in a medium size bowl. Add 1/4 stick of butter and 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons ginger (according to taste), salt and pepper (according to taste) and add 1/4 cup of half and half; whip with beaters. Bake in oven for approximately 1/2 hour or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and rice.
Spread the chopped chicken over all the vegetables.
Mix together the soup and Cheez Whiz; heat in microwave.
Spread on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: rice pudding(top of stove)
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Add vanilla. Serve hot or cold.

title: mushroom-egg quiche(great for a brunch; large serving)
directions: Saute mushrooms and scallions; sprinkle with flour.
Add cream and seasonings.

title: baked green beans
directions: In a 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir soup, milk and soy sauce. Mix in green beans and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Top with remaining onion rings after 25 minutes.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab meat.
Add egg, bread, worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, baking powder, salad dressing and Old Bay.
Shape into balls and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat and drain on towels.

title: pasta with basil and sweet pepper
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and pepper; saute 3 minutes.
Add water, bouillon cube and basil; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vinegar.
Toss with pasta.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Smash shrimp with a fork; squeeze lemon juice over shrimp.
Set aside.
Cream together sour cream and cream cheese; mix in celery and onions.
Stir in shrimp.
Sprinkle pepper over top for decoration.
Best if chilled 2 or more hours before serving.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: waybury hot fruit compote
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for at least 1 hour before serving.
The longer it bakes, the better it is.

title: lemon taffy
directions: Boil sugar with vinegar and water until spoonful dropped in water hardens.
Remove from heat.
Don't stir for it makes it go to sugar.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into buttered pan until it is ready to pull.
Pulling will mix flavoring enough.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Chop chestnuts, onions and parsley.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Add tomatoes, soup, picante sauce and chili powder.
Mix well.
Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1/2 tortilla strips.
Top with 1/2 chicken. Spread 1/2 the vegetable mixture over the chicken.
Repeat the layers and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: turnip carrot slaw
directions: Combine vegetables and raisins.
Mix salad dressing, sour cream and lime juice.
Pour over slaw mixture and chill.

title: peppermint ice cream
directions: In a 6-quart ice cream freezer can stir half and half, condensed milk, milk, vanilla and 1 cup candy.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.
(I usually let it chill 4 to 5 hours.)
Then freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.
Just before freezing time is completed, add the other cup of crushed peppermints.
(It always takes a long time to freeze.)
Ice cream will be soft.

title: hot cha cha
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, green chilies and canned chili; heat until warmed through.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder; add milk.
Pour mixture in baking dish, then pour fruit and juice on top.
May want to add little extra sugar to fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Works great with large sliced peaches.)

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Prepare
rice
mix
according
to
package
directions. Combine prepared rice, chicken, beans, soup, mayonnaise, onion and pepper.
Mix well.	Spoon into slightly greased casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy cranberry-apple sauce
directions: Peel and cut apples (about eighths).
Boil apples in water for 10 minutes.
Add cranberry sauce.
Heat.
Serve warm.

title: chicken casserole mexicana
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Bone and cut in bite-sized pieces.
Put tortillas in boiling chicken stock and soak until wilted (one at a time).
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (overlap edges).
Add chicken, then onion, pepper and cheese. Sprinkle garlic salt to taste over all.
Spread evenly with the two soups.
Crush tomatoes and mix with chili powder.
Pour over all.
Bake at 325°
about 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put 6 bread slices, toasted, cubed and buttered in a baking dish.
Mix pineapple, egg, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over bread cubes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: blackberry pie filling
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill pie crust and bake at 425° for 50 minutes, then bake 15 minutes longer at 350°.

title: pasta with fresh tomato and basil sauce(serves 4)
directions: Rinse the tomatoes; core and cut them into 1/2-inch cubes. Mince the garlic.
Mix the tomatoes, garlic, olive oil and red wine vinegar in a bowl.
Season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes.
Refrigerate the sauce for at least 30 minutes.

title: you're lucky if there's any left dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and finely chopped nuts together and spread like a graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Cool completely.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and one tub of Cool Whip; beat and spread on crust. Beat the instant pudding with milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread the remaining tub of Cool Whip on pudding layer. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Put zucchini through coarse blade of meat grinder or use food processor.
Put zucchini, onions, green peppers, red peppers, hot peppers and salt together.
Soak overnight.
Drain and rinse. Drain well again.
Put in canning kettle and add balance of ingredients. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and boil for 30 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare beef pot pie and mashed potatoes as directed on packages.
In ovenproof dish layer beef pot pie, then mashed potatoes; top with cheese.
Place in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
Eat and enjoy.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Put into crock-pot. Add the beans, onion, green pepper and barbecue sauce (do not stir).
Cook on high 2 to 3 hours or on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into balls on surface, dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Remove 1 cup dry cake mix from the box of yellow cake mix. Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup oleo until crumbly.
Set aside for topping.

title: lo-cal lo-fat cola cake
directions: Mix cola with cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Spread melted butter in a casserole dish.
Grate cheese. Crunch crackers.
Boil vegetables for 25 minutes.
Put half of vegetables in dish.
Layer with half of cheese, then half of crackers.
Repeat layers ending with crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pimento cheese dessert
directions: Mix cheese and juice real well.
Add marshmallows and stir well.
Cut up oranges; add to mixture.
Let set a few minutes until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts.
Pour into long baking dish; refrigerate until firm.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, oleo and chocolate in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Put in rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop on wax paper and let harden.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add nuts or raisins (optional).

title: pumpkin pie bars
directions: Cut margarine into dry cake mix until it forms small crumbs. Reserve 1/3 of the crumb mixture. Press remaining 2/3's in the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 pan, for crust. Mix eggs, milk and sugar. Add pumpkin and spices, blend well. Pour over crust. Top with remaining 1/3 crumb mixture and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: dill potatoes
directions: Slice or dice boiled potatoes with skin on. Add onion, green pepper and dill. Stir in salad dressing. Let marinate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef; stir in taco sauce.
In a small bowl, combine corn and onion.
In a casserole dish, layer half the corn mixture, half the beef mixture, half olives and half cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes, until heated through.
To serve, crumble tortilla shells on plate; top with casserole.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: twinkie-type frosting
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, flour and milk together in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring until thick and boiling.
Cool to room temperature.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine shrimp, mushrooms, celery, onions, green pepper, hard-cooked eggs, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Spoon into ungreased, 9 x 13-inch baking dish or 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potato skins but do not peel.
Boil 20 to 30 minutes or microwave 8 to 12 minutes and let stand 1 minute before removing from microwave.
After either method of cooking, remove skins and slice, cube or mash.
If using canned sweet potatoes, cooking is not necessary.
Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in ungreased shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; drizzle over potatoes.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until glazed and thoroughly heated.
Garnish with mini marshmallows, coconut, peanuts or Macadamia nuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fuzzy navel freeze
directions: Combine milk, peaches, orange juice concentrate, ice cubes and Schnapps in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.
Add yogurt and process just until blended. Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Leave some pecan pieces out so you can sprinkle on top of mixture.
Chill overnight or at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Stir together the soup and milk, then combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir, then top with 1/2 cup Durkee French fried onions or seasoned bread crumbs.
Continue to bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until hot.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, heat bacon and pepper or onion for 3 to 4 minutes on High or until bacon is crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat, covered with waxed paper, on High until bubbly.
Turn power to Medium-low.
Heat, covered, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: soy garlic steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
In glass dish, marinate steak in soy-garlic mixture.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water with sugar.
Set aside.
In large bowl, add flour, soda, baking powder and salt. With a pastry blender, by hand cut Crisco into mixture.
Add milk and softened yeast.
Stir until well blended.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into biscuits, using a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Yields 24 biscuits.
(Dough may be stored in refrigerator and used as needed.)
Will keep for about a week if covered.
Remove from refrigerator about 30 minutes before cooking.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut together and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, flour, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa, egg, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts.
Stir evenly over prepared crust.
Top
with semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Yield: 24 to 36 bars.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
If batter is sticky, add more flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
(Cookie does not spread out.)
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal and vanilla and mix well.
Add peanuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper to cool.

title: lemon dessert
directions: For crust, mix flour, margarine and nuts together and put into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool. For filling, mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 small carton of Cool Whip. Spread on crust. Stir milk into instant lemon Jell-O pudding, mix and pour over cream cheese mixture. Put 1 small carton (4 oz.) Cool Whip on top. Chill for several hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Omit salt. Drain and add other ingredients, reserving a small amount of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix the 2 mixes together and cook.
Crumble and layer in bottom of dish.

title: beef stew
directions: Dredge the beef cubes in the flour, with pepper and salt, until well coated.
Heat oil and add coated beef cubes.
Brown meat.
Add water, onion and bouillon.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 30-45 minutes.
Add other ingredients and cook until carrots and potatoes are tender. Adjust seasoning to taste by adding more Worcestershire sauce, bouillon, salt or pepper.
If the stew seems too runny bring it to a boil, mix a paste of water and flour, add some hot stew liquid and then pour back into the stew stirring constantly until the consistency is acceptable.

title: lunchtime chicken and vegetables
directions: Combine the peas, carrots, cauliflower, corn and broccoli in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until all vegetables are heated through.
Carefully uncover and add chicken, oil and seasoning mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Toss gently and serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon breakfast bites
directions: In bowl, combine and cut in flour, cereal, sugar, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Stir in milk.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: corn meal muffin
directions: Mix buttermilk, soda, sugar and salt together.
Then add meal and mix.
Beat in egg.
Add oil.
Bake in well greased square pan or muffin pans at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lime parfait
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved; add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Pour over cereal and nuts and stir well.
Pour out on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli, cut it up and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and mushrooms. Put aside a large handful of cheese (to sprinkle on top).
Fold the rest of the cheese into the mixture.
Spoon mixture on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top to cook.
Cook for 45 to 55 minutes, until top is golden at 350°.

title: all purpose dinner gravy
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add broth and water.
Cook until thickened 10 to 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup stirring constantly until fully blended.
Cook another 15 minutes.

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Cook next 3 ingredients in pan for 7 to 8 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together in casserole. Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: tuna spread
directions: Blend all
ingredients until smooth.
Serve with crackers or use for spreading on small party sandwiches.

title: spirit balls(about 75)
directions: Chop dates finely.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container in a cool spot.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour once; add baking powder and salt and sift again. Add butter to milk; add flour and stir carefully until all flour is damp and dough is soft.
Drop by teaspoon on chicken gravy.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place the ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole in the following order:
1/2 of the crumbs, sauerkraut, beef and cheese. Top with dressing (Thousand Island and mayonnaise blended) and cover with sliced tomatoes.
Melt butter; mix with remaining crumbs and place on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream 1 cup margarine and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and 1 teaspoon salt; stir in rolled oats.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Set aside while you make filling.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Mix milk and water in saucepan.
Add salt.
Heat slowly at medium heat until milk begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Add oysters, cook slowly until milk comes to slow boil again.

title: oven-fried okra
directions: Wash okra; drain.
Cut off tip ends; cut okra into 1/2-inch slices.
Soak in buttermilk.
Dredge in cornmeal.
Lightly coat a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
Spread okra in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large stew pan.
Completely dissolve the flour.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle the croutons on top of the casserole and the Parmesan on the croutons.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Place under the broiler a minute or so to brown lightly.

title: quick franks and potatoes
directions: Put small amount cooking oil in oblong Pyrex dish.
Peel and slice onion.
Clean bell pepper and slice.
Put onion and bell pepper in dish; place in a 350° oven.
Let cook lightly.
While this is cooking, peel and quarter potatoes and simmer in pot on top of stove.
Don't cook potatoes until done, just so they can be stuck with a fork very slightly.
Add potatoes to onion and pepper; add the hot dogs that have been cut into 3 pieces each. Add tomato sauce, plus 1/2 can water.
Cook until potatoes and dogs are done, about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple tart
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix orange jello.
Chill and add crushed pineapple and 1 small container of Cool Whip.
Mix and put 1/3 of mixture in bottom of 2-quart oblong dish.
Add a layer of graham crackers.
Repeat layers of mixture and graham crackers 2 more times.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with crushed graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
No meringue.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: albacore with rice
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tuna and cheese; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in tuna and 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with remaining cheese, just before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Measure water into small bowl.
Sprinkle onions over water and stir.
Add soy sauce, sweetener, garlic, pepper and sesame seed. Stir to combine.
Coat chicken pieces with mixture.
Place on rack and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion, peppers and beef.
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Cover and cook over low heat about 60 minutes.
Add kidney beans. Cook about 20 minutes.

title: frozen lemon bisque
directions: Whip whites stiff with 1/4 cup sugar. Beat yolks with juice of 2 lemons. Add 3/4 cup sugar, pinch of salt and grated rind. Fold all together and spread in a 9 x 13 Pyrex in which is spread 1 cup graham cracker crumbs. Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs on top. Freeze. Optional: Top with Cool Whip or cherries to serve.

title: chicken salad(orient express)
directions: Bring stock to boil.
Add breasts, reduce heat and poach until chicken is cooked about 10 minutes.
Remove from broth and cool. Discard skin and bones; cut meat into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine chicken with mayonnaise, sour cream, apples, celery, almonds, raisins, parsley and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Arrange lettuce leaves and tomato slices on platter.
Top with chicken salad and sprinkle with vinaigrette.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Cook together 5 or 10 minutes.

title: garlic cheese
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Add garlic, chopped very fine, and nuts.
Sprinkle hands and wax paper with paprika. Form into a roll and chill.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish, layer the rhubarb, sugar, dry jello and dry cake mix, in that order.
Pour the cup of water over all and scatter the pieces of butter over the top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until cake part is lightly browned.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Sprinkle tapioca into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add meat, onion, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Pour tomato juice over the mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Cook onions in 1 teaspoon salt and enough boiling water to cover onions.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes until nearly tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut a slice from the top of each and scoop out the center, leaving an outside shell about a 1/2-inch thick.
Chop pulp.
Saute mushrooms, onions and peppers in butter about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, cream, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fill the shells with the mixture and place in a shallow pan which contains the 1/4 cup of boiling water.
Add cheese to top of each onion.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated oven at 350°
over 30 minutes.

title: easy stewed tomatoes
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Crumble biscuits or bread and add to mixture.
Cover and cook in a saucepan over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: hash browns
directions: Heat the chicken soup, water, onions, sour cream, shredded cheese and melted oleo.
Place in baking dish with the hash browns.

title: savory spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, saute onion, pepper and garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add meat and brown; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, sugar and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes. Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Serve with hot spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg-stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve zucchini lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp to make 1 cup; set aside.
Place zucchini shells, cut side down, in large skillet.
Add the water.
Simmer, covered, until just tender, 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain and turn cut side up in same skillet.
Sprinkle with a little salt.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine water, 1/4 cup salsa, margarine and stuffing mix in 2-quart baking pan.
Arrange chicken on the stuffing.
Pour remaining salsa over chicken.
Cover pan loosely.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese and continue baking for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tiny's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Yields 4 gallons.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all together and stir.
Grease a 12-inch heavy iron frying pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans in salted water; drain (if using canned beans, omit salt).
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour mixture over beans.
Add 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can French fried onions and pimento.
Bake 5 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: fudge cookie salad(mandarin orange salad)
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and oranges. Add cookies before serving.
Save a few for top.

title: mexican mount
directions: Brown ground meat and add taco seasoning.
Keep warm.
Place other ingredients in separate bowls.
Place a mound of corn chips on plate.
Pile on other ingredients.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon and brandy with melted butter.
Mix the mixture lightly with apples.
Place in pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust; make slashes in top crust to allow steam to escape.
Seal ends and flute edges.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes, or until crust is lightly brown.

title: vegetized soy grits
directions: Have cooked grits as dry as possible.
Add the following sauce and serve immediately when well browned.
Add broth, soy sauce and water to oil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add cooked grits and cook until well browned.
Stir constantly.
Serve hot with vegetables.

title: pork chop-green bean casserole
directions: Brown chops and place them in a long baking dish.
Pour green beans over pork chops.
Dice onion and sprinkle over green beans. Pour soup over green beans (add a little milk if desired to make soup thinner).
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and cube with skins on.
Cube cheese and sprinkle on top.
Add onion, pimento and bread cubes.
Melt oleo and stir in onion and garlic salt.
Pour this over potato mixture. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are warm and cheese melts.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix well all ingredients in a bowl.
Spoon into salt shakers. Can be used on almost everything except fruit, cakes, pies, puddings, etc.

title: orzo casserole
directions: Saute and brown the first four ingredients.
Draw fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mylene's oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, shortening, egg and milk until creamy.
Add all other ingredients (except flour, oats and chips) and stir.
Add flour; stir.
Add oats and chips; combine well.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold all of the ingredients together gently and spoon into crusts.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: aminell's coconut pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and cook until thick. Remove from heat; add vanilla and coconut. Stir well and pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine all.
Heat slowly until cheese melts.
Do not boil!

title: treasure filled coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Using shortening, grease 12-cup fluted tube pan (nonstick).
Also, combine sugar, peel and nuts.
Set aside.

title: mile high dessert
directions: Combine egg whites, strawberries, sugar and lemon juice in a very large bowl and beat with electric mixer until stiff and fluffy, about 15 minutes.
It becomes very high!
Fold the Cool Whip into the strawberry mixture.
Spoon over the crumb crust. Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: nanny-grammy's mushroom lentil chowder(crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart electric crockery cooker.
Cover.
Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with homemade bread or biscuits.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in 8-inch square pan.
Blend and spread last four ingredients; pour over the apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gracious meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a loaf pan.
Heat oven to 375°. Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.
Yummy!

title: prune cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add all other ingredients and drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Add soup, mushrooms and 1 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth.
In a large greased dish, layer spaghetti, chicken sauce and cheese. Repeat if dish is deep.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. May freeze.

title: bacon guacamole dip
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir half of bacon into dip.
Sprinkle remaining on top.
Garnish with olive slices.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with chips.

title: lemon barbecued chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; set aside. Sift remaining ingredients together, then add egg mixture. Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired. Bake in 350° preheated oven for 1 hour or until done. Makes 2 loaves.

title: scotch casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Blend milk, soup, beef, cheese, onion and garlic salt.
Grease large casserole and alternate macaroni and beef.
Mix layers and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.

title: kool-aid cookie icing
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with powdered sugar.
Mix in other ingredients until creamy.
Spread on cooled cookies.

title: 100 cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix sugars, margarine, oil, cereal, coconut, oats, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips or Brickle.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These cookies stay crisp a long time and make a lot of cookies.
Our family favorite.

title: cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into shortening mixture alternating with milk.
Pour into greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Spoon over batter drained berries or sliced peaches.
Sprinkle 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar over fruit.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll dough from 1 package of rolls.
Press into prepared pan.
Press to eliminate holes. Soften cream cheese.
Beat until creamy.
Add sugar and egg yolk. Spread over dough in pan.
Form another rectangle of dough from second package and place on top of cheese.
Brush top with egg white.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: cinnamon apple bread pudding
directions: In medium bowl blend eggs, sugar, milk, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, 1 tablespoon of butter and vanilla.
Add bread; mix well. Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dip apple slices in remaining 1 tablespoon butter and arrange slices on top. Set casserole in a larger dish and place in a preheated 350° oven.
Pour enough hot water in pan to come up 3/4 inch.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with Orange Sauce.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together 4 times the sugar, cocoa, baking powder, flour and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Ice with Chocolate Deluxe Icing.

title: red hot jelly
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine juice and sugar.
Stir well.
Add margarine and candy.
Stirring constantly, bring to a rolling boil over high heat.
Stir in liquid pectin.
Stirring constantly, return to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Skim foam from top of jelly with a large metal spoon.
Fill sterilized jars to within 1/4-inch of tops.
Wipe jars and seal. Store in refrigerator.
Makes a great gift.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together slowly, stirring all the while. Cook until mixture turns transparent; let cool completely.
Pour mixture into pie shells that are filled with sliced or whole strawberries.
Add Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and beat until creamy. Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, sifted.
Grease pan; use angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May add raisins, nuts or dried dates, if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cherry filling on bottom. Layer pineapple and dry cake mix, melted butter and coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add Kool-Aid while hot.
Cool and add juice.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 50 cups.

title: velveeta fudge (large)
directions: Melt cheese and butter together and add vanilla in a large bowl. Mix powdered sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Pour in cheese and butter mixture.
It will be stiff, so be prepared to use your hands.
Roll out on freezer paper to desired thickness.

title: lite and luscious chocolate dream pie
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip together.
Add cream cheese; blend well.
Add 3/4 cup strawberries to mixture; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with strawberries and a few nuts if desired.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Grease loaf pan.
In loaf pan, put in a layer of cooked spaghetti, then add a layer of Kraft cheese, followed by a layer of hot dogs.
Continue this layering until 1-inch from top of loaf pan.
Pour over a can of condensed milk until just covered.
Bake at 350° until layer of cheese on top is beginning to brown.
Take from oven.
Let sit for 15 minutes. Turn out on platter and slice as needed.
Thick slices.

title: dressing
directions: Grind or chop seasonings.
Drain oysters and keep water.
Soak bread in oyster water.
Use a small amount of cooking oil in pot and add everything except bread and oysters.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until grease rises to top (about 40 minutes). Squeeze bread and add to mixture.
Let cook down.
Chop and add oysters. Add parsley and shallots.
Cook on low fire until oysters are done (not long).

title: pepper steak
directions: Dip steak strips in flour.
In large skillet, saute steak in 1/2 the butter for about 2 minutes.
Remove meat.
Add remaining butter to skillet and saute peppers, onion, garlic and mushrooms 5 minutes; add tomatoes and bouillon.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, wine and soy sauce.
Add to skillet.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add meat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sausage cornbread dressing
directions: Make cornbread mix as directed.
Cool.
In a large skillet, saute sausage meat, stirring, until browned.
Lift out with slotted spoon.
In drippings in skillet, saute celery, onion, green pepper and parsley until tender 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Boil and pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
This can be frozen. Will stay good in refrigerator for a long time.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Combine the raisins, soda and boiling water. Cover and let set overnight in a big bowl.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in pan. Set aside.
Peel potatoes, cook and mash.
In Dutch oven layer ground beef on bottom, soup and mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in sweet potatoes.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add alternately with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Grease 1 1/2-inch muffin tin and fill 2/3 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Slice thin.
Mix together with original Ranch salad dressing.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and flour.
Beat well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Put in greased bread pan.
Top with 2 tablespoons each of the oleo, sugar and flour plus 1 teaspoon cinnamon crumbled together.
Press in slightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Crumble half of cake in bottom of trifle bowl. Pour kahlua on top.
Layer chocolate pudding and Cool Whip.
Cover with crunched up Heath bars.
Repeat: cake, pudding, Cool Whip, candy.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasoning. Coat chicken with flour mixture. In skillet, melt butter or margarine and fry chicken until brown on all sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup water.
Lower heat and simmer, stirring frequently. Simmer for about 20 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Can be served over rice or noodles.

title: italian vegetable casserole
directions: Saute hamburg and drain. Cut up vegetables and place in large baking pan.
Place hamburg on top of veggies. Pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Spread Mozzarella cheese, then American cheese in strips then sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover loosely with foil. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Prepare a day ahead and reheat for most flavor.

title: apple-bavarian torte
directions: For Crust:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and vanilla in medium bowl.
Cut in butter, using pastry blender, until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake until golden, about 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream cheese, then add sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Add Cool Whip and beat well. Pour into crust and refrigerate. Add any topping you like.

title: easy bean soup
directions: Remove fat from ham left on bone.
Put in 6-quart Dutch oven or stock pot.
Cover with water (about 3 to 4 quarts, depending on size of bone).
Simmer for about 3 hours, skimming off grease. Chop canned tomatoes; wash celery and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Wash and peel potatoes; cut into eighths.
Add to broth.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked.
Rinse beans; add to vegetables and broth.
Simmer until beans are heated through; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with salad and hard rolls.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Trim off fat and skin.
Mix all other ingredients in bottom of Dutch oven.
Add meat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 6 hours.
Take meat out and allow to cool; shred.
Use sauce on beef or serve on rice.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix sliced peaches, melted margarine and vanilla together. Pour into baking dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar together. Drizzle on top of peach mixture.

title: cake pan potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes like for French fries.
Put in greased cake pan.
Pour other ingredients over potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on a little before done.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare ground beef and taco sauce according to directions on package.
Shred lettuce.
Chop tomatoes and drain.
Mix together all ingredients except taco chips.
At last minute before serving, crush taco chips and toss with other ingredients.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into iron skillet.
Cook at 400° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir together light brown sugar, granulated sugar, water, corn syrup and butter.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap, turning back one section to vent steam. Microwave at High setting (100% power) 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Cover again, and microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in confectioners sugar until well blended. Continue stirring for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Quickly drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto buttered waxed paper (if mixture becomes too thick to drop from a spoon, stir in a few drops hot water).
Let pralines stand until set.
Carefully remove pralines from waxed paper.
Store between layers of foil in airtight container.
Makes about 20 pralines.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, bananas and eggs.
Stir well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Blend well.
Add walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: funny faces
directions: Decorate individual dessert dishes with paper cut-outs, if desired.

title: cinnamon toasties
directions: Spread cottage cheese over toasted bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Broil for a few minutes.
Top with fruit.

title: honey barbecue sauce
directions: In a bowl, whisk together the honey, sherry, soy sauce and garlic.
The sauce may be made 1 week in advance and kept covered and chilled.
Makes 8 servings.
Serving size:
1/4 cup. Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple chunks, saving juice. Melt butter over low heat (or in oven) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Place pineapple chunks evenly over butter and sugar, then cherries and pecans.

title: tangy artichoke dip
directions: In small bowl mix artichokes, salad dressing, cheese, peppers and parsley until well blended.
Cover; chill until serving time. Garnish with parsley.
Serve as a dip with pretzel chips.

title: fruit compote(method:  foil)
directions: On a sheet of double foil, place pineapple, then cover with remaining ingredients.
Wrap up with a long tail to lift off fire. Place on coals for 10 minutes.
Divide into 8 pieces.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter; mix with crushed vanilla wafers. Press in bottom of dish.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla, 2 sticks soft butter and sugar with mixer at high speed for 2 minutes. Spread on top of crust.
Sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh.
Add sliced bananas; sprinkle again with Fruit-Fresh.
Add drained pineapple; spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place
chicken	(boiled
and
cut into small pieces) in bottom of
baking
dish.	Pour
chicken
soup
and broth over chicken. Mix together flour, buttermilk and melted margarine. Pour over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Slice thin (on slaw cutter fine) cucumbers and onions.
Put in bowl, add salt.
Let set 2 hours.
Drain well.
Add sugar and vinegar. Mix.
Put into containers.
Freeze.

title: orange juice muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Mix together the Bisquick, 2 tablespoons sugar, egg, orange peel and orange juice.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle about 1/2 teaspoon over tops of each muffin.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and remove from broth. Add cream of chicken soup. Stir well. Tear the flour tortillas in pieces and drop in broth. Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until tortillas plump up.
Add chicken. You're done.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain tuna, peas and noodles.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a large buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can add chopped celery or green pepper.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Spread the scallops in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in pan; add the onions, celery, and mushrooms.
Let stand a few minutes at low heat.
Make white sauce with 1/4 cup melted butter, 1/4 cup flour, and 2 cups milk.
Add this to the ingredients fried in butter.
Spread this mixture onto the scallops.
Cover with the bread crumbs, grated cheese and melted butter.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes or until it is a golden color.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain, debone and skin salmon.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons chopped parsley.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Stir remaining ingredients together in order as listed. Mix well in large bowl. Add yeast and mix well. Refrigerate dough at least 12 hours, covered.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Cook potatoes in pan in salted water until tender.
Drain. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in vinegar, parsley, sugar, paprika, salt and pepper.
Combine potatoes, bacon and onion mixture.
Toss gently.
Serve warm with pork and sauerkraut.

title: mexican vegetable casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine corn, onion, green pepper and water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Do not drain.

title: ham potato scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes with sauce mix, boiling water and butter.	Stir in milk, ham and beans.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes or until the potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sully's sausage soup
directions: Brown onion and sausage in soup pan, then slice sausage into thin pieces.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
(Crush tomatoes with spoon.)
Reduce heat to simmer; cook until zucchini is tender.
Serve hot with cheese sprinkled over top.
For healthier soup, cool and skim fat off top.
Freeze what isn't used.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave the potatoes 15 minutes or until done but not too soft.
Cut the potatoes at the top just enough to scoop out the inside, leaving the shell.
Add the sour cream, butter, 3/4 cup of the cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend the mixture until it is smooth.
Fill the shells with the mixture, then top them with the remaining cheese and chives.
Microwave for 2 minutes; serve hot.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Mix soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together; set aside.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasonings.
Put 1/2 of Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of meat mixture, all of cheese, then both cans beans, another layer of chips, then other 1/2 of meat mixture on top.
Pour soup mixture to cover top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Season chops with salt. Place in large baking dish. Top each chop with onion slice. Place 1 1/2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup on top. Add the water and bake, covered, for 2 hours. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally. Yields 4 to 8 servings.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet until meat is cooked.
Add mushroom soup, milk, chiles.
Mix well.
Lay slices of cheese on top.
Cover in electric skillet or slow oven.
Heat thoroughly until cheese melts at 300 - 350. 5 large servings.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can fried onions. Pour into casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: sicilian chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until slightly tender, about 10 minutes.
Cut chicken in 2-inch pieces.
Add to onion mixture.
Cook, turning chicken frequently, until pinkness is gone. Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until heated thorough or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: peppered salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup gravy, ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt. Shape into 6 oval patties.
In skillet, brown patties in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: linda's cherry pie
directions: In small saucepan, combine 3/4 cup of the sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon until well blended.
Drain cherries; reserve 1 cup of juice.
Stir cherry juice into sugar mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until mixture thickens.
Add remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Stir in cherries.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Add pie filling.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust (or a lattice); cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken packets
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, chives, milk and salt in a medium mixing bowl to make filling.
Each tube will contain 4 rectangles of dough with a diagonal perforation.
Press dough along each perforation so the rectangle halves will not separate.
Place about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture into center of each rectangle. Fold dough over the filling; pinch the edges to seal tightly.
Dip each packet in melted margarine; coat with crouton crumbs.
Place packets on baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 8 packets.
Good hot or cold.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in water and salt in a tightly covered pan for 5 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and add to cooked celery.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with cashews if desired.

title: cake-n-bake cookies
directions: Place dry cake mix in a large bowl, then add softened butter and egg. Blend thoroughly.
Place dough on lightly floured pastry sheet and roll with rolling pin to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into desired shape.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen 2-inch cookies or 12 to 15 (4-inch) cookies.

title: mrs. jessie's broccoli soup
directions: Bring broccoli to boil and cook according to directions on package.
Cook first 2 ingredients until onion is tender; add to broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted and soup is hot, stirring constantly.

title: fresh strawberry cream pie(no bake)
directions: With mixer, beat cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and beat just until blended and smooth.
Spread this mixture into the pie shell.
Mix berries and glaze together and spread over cream cheese mixture in the pie shell.
Refrigerate for about an hour and then serve.
Delicious.

title: slaw
directions: Heat to boiling everything except the cabbage.
Cool and pour over cabbage.
Chill.
Will keep for a few days if refrigerated.

title: ground beef a la donna
directions: Fry onion, pepper and beef together in a skillet; drain.
Add salt, pepper, basil, oregano and onion soup mix to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all together and cook 5 minutes to blend flavors.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 45 minutes (until cabbage is tender).
Serve over rice, beans or pasta.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Boil and drain squash. Mix all ingredients and place in a buttered casserole. Dot with butter and bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Tastes best when prepared a day in advance.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and chill.

title: pineapple turnover biscuits
directions: Drain the pineapple, saving the syrup.
Combine the pineapple, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Divide the mixture into 10 greased muffin cups.
Place a walnut half on each.
Add one teaspoon of pineapple syrup to each.
Top with a biscuit.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until the biscuits are done.
Invert pan immediately on a serving plate.
Cool for 1 minute before lifting pan.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes. Add the Certo. Boil 1 more minute.
Let set for 5 minutes and put in jars. (Baby food jars are great.)
Cover top with paraffin.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in tube pan, bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Start in cold oven.

title: taco sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until thick, about 1 hour. Stir frequently so it does not stick to bottom of pan.

title: duckling bigarade
directions: In mixing bowl, combine orange marmalade, soy sauce and salt. Roast duckling in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and cook for 30 minutes or until tender.
Baste with half of orange sauce while cooking.
Brown flour in butter over low heat.
Stir in Chablis, wine vinegar and consomme.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly, and then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining orange sauce.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Add pepper.
Peel and cut orange into wedges.
Cook in boiling water for 3 minutes and drain. Remove duckling to warm serving platter.
Garnish with orange wedges.
Pour excess fat off juices in pan.
Add more stock to pan if needed for sauce.
Serve hot in gravy boat.
Serves 4.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer crushed tortilla chips in casserole dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over chips.
Cover with cheese and bake in 425° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, zucchini and oil.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make add 1 cup walnuts or pecans.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Let butter, cocoa and water boil, then mix well.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and put in long cake pan and bake at 350°.
This makes a good cake.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon; remove.
Cook onion in bacon drippings.
Blend flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper in with onion.
Remove from heat; stir in water and vinegar.
Heat until boiling.
Crumble bacon into mixture and stir in cut up potatoes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Make chocolate cake mix according to package.
Bake in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool cake.
Combine cornstarch and milk in pan.
Cook until thick; cover and cool. Cream vanilla, sugar, Crisco and 1/2 cup oleo.
Add to cornstarch mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread onto cool cake.
Melt 1/2 cup and 2 tablespoons oleo and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add powdered sugar, egg and hot water.
Beat well and spread onto cake.
Do quickly, the icing starts to settle immediately.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Chop apples; add sugar and fresh cranberries.
Pour into a 9 x 13 sprayed casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and drop by hand over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix with a spoon flour, powdered sugar and softened butter (not melted).
Press into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, covering bottom and sides to 1/2-inch of edge.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Hand mix the next 5 ingredients for 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until no imprint is left when touched.
Cover and cool overnight.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares. Serves 16.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Cook linguini in boiling water.
Drain.
Meanwhile, saute garlic and onion in olive oil until soft, but not brown.
Toss all ingredients together in pot.
Add sea legs and more oil as needed. Season with Mrs. Dash or Italian seasoning to taste.
Serve warm. Add broccoli if desired.

title: ham, potato and onion casserole
directions: Melt drippings or butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, boiling about 3 minutes. Add seasoning and cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts; add ham, potatoes and onions.
Pour mixture into greased casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: low-fat banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with vegetable spray.
In bowl combine milk, egg substitute, bananas and oil. Stir in cereal.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Mix filling, milk, cream cheese and juice and pour into crust. Let stand until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening, using 2 knives, a pastry cutter or your hands dusted with flour.
Add sufficient buttermilk to make a soft dough.

title: mystery pie
directions: Boil the whole can of milk in water 4 hours; do not open can. Let the can cool in the refrigerator 24 hours or longer.
It will caramelize.
Slice bananas; put in crust.
Mix pecans with caramelized milk and pour over bananas.
Put dairy topping on top. Keep refrigerated.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine All-Bran and milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add grated carrot; fold in. Pour mixture evenly into 12 muffin tins.
Sprinkle a little sugar over each muffin.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and mash ripe avocados.
Mix in sour cream and picante sauce.
If onion is desired, peel and chop onion.
Add to your taste.

title: emily's pie
