directions: Mix the vanilla pudding, pineapple and sour cream together. Then put the vanilla pudding, pineapple and the sour cream in the graham cracker or shortbread crust.
ENJOY.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat will blended through.

title: white bean dip
directions: Pulse all ingredients except chives in food processor until a smooth paste forms and transfer to a bowl.
Serve on bruschetta and garnish with chopped chives.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix honey, orange juice, orange peel, allspice and cranberry sauce in small bowl.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over chicken breasts.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 15 minutes, covered.
Turn chicken pieces, pour on remaining sauce, cover, continue to bake for 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Place chicken breasts in 3 quart baking dish.
Add all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Two minutes before taking dish out, sprinkle the other half of fried onions on chicken.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese to serve.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute green peppers in olive oil for 2 minutes on medium heat. Layer vegetables in order over peppers.
Cover with tomato sauce. Sprinkle parsley, sweet basil and minced garlic on top.
Cover until there is enough juice to baste.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Do not disturb layers (salt and pepper each layer, if desired).
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and let melt.
Serve like a pie.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and beat until smooth.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all together, then add persimmon last.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese-filled italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, spaghetti mix and ketchup.
In large, shallow pan, shape into loaf, placing cheese in center and sealing edges tightly.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, blending at low until crumbly. Stir in nuts. Press 2 3/4 cup mixture into ungreased 9x13 pan. To remaining mixture, add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla & egg. Blend well. Stir in apples and spoon evenly over base. Bake at 350 for 25-35 min. until done.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together well and store in an airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Place green tomatoes and onion in large bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice and let stand 2 hours.
Stir once or twice. Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil, then add vegetables and cook until color changes.
Then, put in jars and seal.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add apples alternately with flour.
Add 1 cup pecans.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: welcome school's chicken pie
directions: *I use chicken breasts (4 or more).

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Whip the heavy cream until slightly thickened and fold in the sugar. Fold in the eggs and vanilla. Sift the flour with the baking powder and salt and fold into the creamed mixture.
Place in 2 greased layer pans or 1 loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven and cool. Fill and frost with Seven-Minute Icing.

title: "mock" strawberry jam
directions: Peel figs, mash and measure.
Add sugar and Karo to figs. Cook for 5 minutes at rapid boil.
Add dry jello and cook for 3 minutes longer at a good boil.
Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Add ice. Makes approximately 30 servings.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Dice cheese and add to mixture.
Add oregano, onion and garlic salt.
Spread on slices of bread.
Place on cookie sheets and warm until cheese bubbles. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk, flour, dates, pecans, coconut and orange slice candy. Mix by hand.
Grease tube pan, pour ingredients into pan and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
While cake is cooking, mix orange juice and powdered sugar and pour over cake as soon as it is removed from oven.
Let cake stand overnight before serving.

title: tasty toss-up
directions: Prepare rotini according to directions on package; drain.
In a large bowl combine rotini, tuna, celery, cucumbers, tomato, green pepper and onions.
In a small bowl, blend together Italian dressing, mayonnaise, mustard and seasoning.
Add to salad mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill.
Toss before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: special coconut cake
directions: Make cake by package directions.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans. Let cool; slice layers making 4.
Combine sugar with sour cream and coconut until smooth; set 1 cup aside.
Spread remainder between layers.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix baking soda and buttermilk. Slowly add liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix in jam, blending completely.
Bake on 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy cherry cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, figs and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dip
directions: Brown meat; melt cheese in microwave.
Watch so as to not boil over.
Cook in crock-pot.
Freezes well.
May add doubled cheese or drained Ro-Tel.

title: seafood sauce picante
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Add tomato paste.
Add dash of sugar and let boil.
Add rest of ingredients and let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
If too watery, add 1 tablespoon of flour, dissolved in water, to thicken.
Serves 12 to 15.
Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, milk, sifted dry ingredients and rolled oats.
Stir only enough to mix.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: great pimento cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients together to form a good consistency. Add sugar according to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: peach icebox pie
directions: Line 8-inch dish with graham cracker crumbs.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg well and spread over crumbs.
Arrange sliced peaches to cover creamed mixture.
Whip cream and spread over peaches, sprinkling crumbs over top.
Place in refrigerator and chill overnight.

title: fried rice with shrimp
directions: Cut shrimp into small pieces.
Mix with cornstarch and salt. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok to 400°.
Stir-fry shrimp and green onions until pink, about 30 seconds.
Remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok, pour in beaten eggs.
Scramble fine.
Remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok and add rice, soy sauce and ginger. Stir-fry until thoroughly heated.
Add eggs, shrimp and rice wine. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Recipe is also good without shrimp or good with leftover pork or beef.

title: dippety doo dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; warm in microwave.
Mix well.

title: irish cream
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Fill with ice.
Blend until ice is crushed, then serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Prepare rolls according to package; put triangles on pan and pinch together.
Cook according to directions.
Let cool.

title: microwave potatoes anna
directions: Thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Alternate potatoes, onion and soup (which has been mixed with water) in casserole dish. Salt and pepper each layer.
Pour melted margarine over all. Microwave for 15 to 20 minutes on High (until potatoes are tender).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 5 to 8.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, beans, 1 cup of picante sauce, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, eggs, cumin and salt; mix well.
Press into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Carefully pour off drippings.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup picante sauce and brown sugar; mix well.
Spread over surface of meat loaf.
Continue baking 15 minutes; remove and let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccalie
directions: Combine eggs, cheese and mayo.
Place broccoli in buttered dish. Pour mixture over it. Melt butter in pan and brown
bread in butter. Put over broccoli and cheese mixture. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party casserole
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and pinch edges to form one sheet.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Put a pan of water on high heat on stove.
Combine hamburger, egg, milk,
Italian seasoning, bacon bits, garlic powder, onion and bouillon.
Make sure it's mixed well.
Add rice and cracker crumbs.
The mixture has to be dry enough to hold shape so more crackers may be added if needed.
Using a teaspoon, get about 1/2 teaspoon of mixture and make a miniature meatball.
Drop meatballs in boiling water and boil about 5 minutes.
The meatballs could be made ahead of time and kept in the refrigerator until time to serve.
They are good hot or cold.
Yields about 100 meatballs.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease a pie pan.
Line with crescent rolls and crushed chips. Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add water and seasoning mix and simmer a few minutes.
Pour on top of chips.
Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Top with more chips.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown, about 20 minutes.
Before serving, put lettuce and tomatoes on top.
Makes 6 slices.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 1/4 cup hot water.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Whip canned milk and fold into gelatin mixture.
Spread 1 cup of wafers on bottom of large cake dish (9x13) and add remaining crushed wafers on top of mixture.

title: mom's chicken dressing
directions: Cook stewing hen until tender in plenty of water to be used as broth later.
When cool, skin and debone.
Refrigerate.
Cook 1 large skillet of self-rising corn bread, using 3 to 4 eggs.
When done, remove from skillet to large mixing bowl.
Add 6 thick or 8 thin slices of bread.
Pour enough broth to cover. Dissolve the soup in more broth (1 can).
Pour this over bread.
Use poultry seasoning and 2 bouillon chicken cubes, if needed, to improve taste.
Set mixture aside for bread to soften.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In one container, mix olives, chilies, milk, soups and meat. Layer in a cake pan:
1/4 sauce, 1/2 tortillas, 1/4 sauce, 1/2 cheese, 1/4 sauce, 1/2 tortillas, 1/4 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into logs (3 or 4).
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil.
Wrap well and freeze until ready to bake.
Slice 1/4 inch and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour margarine, cocoa and water over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and bake 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet with sides in 375° oven.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a mixing bowl.
Blend well and set aside.
Saute ground chuck and onion until slightly browned.
Drain.
Chop peppers into beef mixture and mix well.

title: blueberry cheese dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix well with margarine and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press into bottom of 9-inch square pan or round cake pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
In medium size flowerpot, beginning with Oreos, alternate layers of pudding mixture and Oreos.
Chill. Add silk flowers and a shovel and serve!!

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening. Beat in eggs and orange juice. Sift together all dry

ingredients and gradually add to liquid mixture. Fold in cranberries and nuts. Turn batter into oiled loaf pan. Makes 2 loaves in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans. Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour or until brown and crusty.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper until done.
Drain.
Beat eggs, milk and black pepper together.
Melt butter in skillet. Add egg mixture.
Cook, without stirring, until eggs begin to set on bottom and around edges.
Using spatula, lift and fold partially cooked eggs so uncooked egg flows underneath.
Cook until done.
Remove from heat.

title: baked lobster and shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs in casserole dish. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Boil these ingredients 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sliced mushrooms and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Let stand.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, salt, onion, soup and water in saucepan.
Bring to boiling, lower heat and cook until potatoes are tender.
Mash. Add milk; heat through and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Chop green onions.
Add onion soup, then mix in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix all together and refrigerate until cold.
Cut out center in sourdough bread; hollow, then add dip.
Save center and break up around to use to dip out spinach dip.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain pasta and while still hot add all the other ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight and stir again before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in the hot milk gradually until smooth.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks until the eggs are mixed into the hot mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes, until it boils and is thick enough to mound.
Pour into bowl. Stir in the vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Put wax paper over filling.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: pie crust miracle
directions: Cut the shortening into flour and salt into small pieces.
Dig hole and add milk.
Stir.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out.

title: country style ribs
directions: Ribs may be parboiled 15 minutes.
Combine ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Thaw butter to degree where peanut butter can be worked into it
and
not
be
lumpy
(use
double boiler).
Add chili powder and
mix well.
Warm these ingredients to melting point and then add salt, pepper, celery seed and vinegar.
Warm the mixture to boiling point, but do not boil.
Let this cool and add juice
of the lemons.
Makes enough sauce for 8 halves of chicken.

title: copper pennies(carrots)
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender. Slice onions and peppers. Combine with remaining ingredients and let set 24 hours before serving.
Can be stored in refrigerator 2 weeks or more.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix orange drink, lemonade mix, tea, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Store in tight-closing jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: corn spoon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gen. norman schwarzkopf's sour cream peach pie
directions: Fill the pie shell with sliced peaches. Blend flour, 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Stir in sour cream and pour mixture over the peaches. Mix together 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over pie. Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana cake
directions: Beat together in mixing bowl the bananas and margarine until creamy. Add eggs and water. Beat well. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon; beat until smooth. Add chopped walnuts. Pour in an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until inserted knife comes out clean. Cool and cut into squares.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Melt
butter in 13 x 9-inch glass oven dish.
Mix cake mix and 2 beaten eggs into melted butter (use fork; mixture will be somewhat dry and stiff).
In a medium bowl, blend together cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Slowly add 10x sugar.
Pour this mixture over cake mixture without stirring.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup 10x sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into small squares.
It is very rich.

title: busy-day cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small mixer bowl, combine all ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Turn into pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool.
Serves 9.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in fry pan.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Line a greased casserole dish with tortillas (that have been softened slightly by frying in 2 tablespoons bacon grease for flavor).
Cover with meat mixture.
Combine soup with milk; pour over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Boil macaroni and drain. In another bowl add oil, red wine vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and crushed red pepper; stir into a dressing.
Pour drained macaroni into dressing mixture and toss good.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss gain.
Chill overnight.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Makes about 2 cups of mix.
Place a well rounded teaspoon of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.

title: chicken spaghetti for company
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes off bone easily.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Drain.
Saute celery, onions, green onions and bell pepper in butter.
Mix sauteed ingredients, canned Ro-Tel, tomatoes, soups, pimento and olives.
Add to spaghetti.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Layer spaghetti mixture, chicken and grated cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (layer at least twice ending with cheese on top).
Bake for 2 hours at 250°.
Recipe makes enough for three baking dishes and freezes well.
Thaw before baking.

title: creamy broccoli and zucchini
directions: In medium saucepan, cook broccoli and zucchini together covered in a small amount of boiling salted water until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
In large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in butter or margarine until onion is tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, parsley, salt and oregano.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Ricotta cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese is nearly melted.
Stir in cooked vegetables.
Heat through.
Place vegetable mixture over hot cooked noodles.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.

title: salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Combine ingredients. Chill until serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Fold Cool Whip, cream cheese and condensed milk together. Then layer into bowl as follows:
cake, whipped cream and then pie filling.

title: crispy cornflake chews
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda. Add oats and flakes; mix well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(Pie will not test done in center).
Cool; cut into wedges.
Top with ice cream and hot fudge sauce.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch greased pan, pour coconut over entire bottom, then pour nuts over that.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour this over coconut and nuts.

title: apple dessert
directions: Peel and slice apples into deep baking dish 2/3 full.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix with apples. Then mix together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, oil, egg, vanilla and salt.
Cover apples with mixture and bake at 350° until apples are soft.
For 1 1/2 quart dish, about an hour.

title: dutch pork chops
directions: Flour pork chops; fry in hot grease in frying pan until rich brown.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add catsup and onion.
Lay potatoes around chops.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: jason's country scramble
directions: In medium-size skillet add butter and melt.
Add bell peppers, onions and ham; saute.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Put everything in a large stew pot except greens.
Dice and slice meat and vegetables.
Put in enough water to cover everything.
Add greens for last 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook for several hours.
Watch water, add more as needed.

title: *broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli; mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.
May add cracker crumbs and butter to top of casserole.

title: dieters delight
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Place in Teflon pan with 1 cup of water.
Sprinkle soy sauce over the chicken.
Add dash of salt and pepper on chicken.
Bring to boil.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 1 hour.
Turn over several times while cooking.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with 4 tablespoons butter.
Press into pie plate and chill.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spoon into chilled crust.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yummy!

title: granola
directions: Put very small dabs of peanut butter on a paper plate.
Stick a toothpick in each; freeze.
Then dip in chocolate syrup and freeze again.
Eat!

title: baked chow mein dish
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and celery.
Add other ingredients. Put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: drop fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa, syrup and milk.
Mix well. Let come to a boil, then cook for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Set in a pan of cold water.
Add vanilla; beat until you can lift by teaspoon onto a greased platter.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in egg whites and then roll in finely chopped walnuts.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down centers with thumb.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Just before serving, fill centers with preserves.
Makes 36.

title: coconut chocolate balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls. Chill.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together. Makes 3 cups.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli as usual.
Cook the rice according to the package directions.
Saute the garlic in the margarine.
Dilute the soup with water from the broccoli (about 1/4 cup of water). Put everything into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into cylinder shape and wrap in wax paper.
Roll until cylinder is about 1 inch in diameter. Refrigerate.
Unwrap and cut into slices.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: wiener sauce
directions: Brown hamburg in pan.
When done, drain grease.
Take tomato paste, water, onions and other ingredients and mix together.
Let simmer on the stove.
When hamburg is drained, add to mixture and simmer for 1 1/2 hours on stove.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Marinate the frog legs in salt, pepper and lemon juice for about 1 hour or more.
Dip legs in egg and roll in bread crumbs. Deep fat fry until golden brown.

title: almond poppy seed bread(this is more like pound cake than bread)
directions: Preset oven to 350° (300° for glass pans).
Grease with Crisco two loaf pans.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix slightly beaten egg, oil, sugar and milk.
Add flour mixture and stir by hand.
Stir in flavoring and poppy seed.
Bake for 1 hour until bread springs back to touch.
(Don't use mixer; bread is too dense.)

title: dot's goop
directions: Brown together beef and onion.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over Fritos.

title: filled cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Cook over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread mixture on this.
Add second layer of crackers on top of this.

title: maple butter icing
directions: Blend together butter and sugar. Add syrup and beat mixture until well blended and fluffy. Frosts one 8-inch layer cake.

title: crusty french bread
directions: Combine shortening, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Add boiling water and cold water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Blend yeast as directed on package.
Add to mixture.
Gradually add flour.
Mix until well blended.
Knead on lightly floured board for 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Shape into long oblong loaves and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until double.
Brush dough with slightly beaten egg white.
Cut top of dough diagonally across top 3 times.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: tennessee jam cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and prepare two 8-inch round or square cake pans. Sift together flour, soda and spices. Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs 1 at a time. Fold in flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, making 3 additions. Stir in preserves, raisins, nuts and jam. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with Caramel Icing. This cake is better if allowed to mellow 2 to 3 days.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Put fruit in bowl; add honey and vanilla.
Toss to mix and coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: mama's quick stew
directions: Heat pot on medium 3 to 5 minutes.
Add oil.
Brown meat, then add sliced onion.
Turn heat to low.
Stir in sauce, 1 sauce can water, dash of pepper and salt.
Cut up carrots and add with peas. Cook 45 minutes, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Add potatoes, if desired.
Cook extra 25 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Remove from skillet, remove excess fat and season with
salt
and pepper.
Set aside.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine biscuit mix, the first 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from pan. Dip tops in melted butter and then in cinnamon/sugar mixture. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring 2 quarts water, cloves and cinnamon to a boil and simmer 20 minutes. Add sugar.
Make tea with 1 additional quart of water and 6 tea bags.
Steep about 5 minutes.
Pour tea into first mixture. Add juices and heat.

title: old fashioned t-cakes
directions: Bake at 400°
to 450° until bottoms brown.

title: potato apple skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add apple, onion and celery.
Stir until coated.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Serve.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce and other ingredients.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic salt on layers.
Top with dressing.

title: oatmeal pie(cheap pecan pie)
directions: Mix; pour into unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti fruit salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool spaghetti.
Drain pineapple and add to spaghetti along with grapes and apples; set aside.
Cook eggs, sugar and lemon juice until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and pour over spaghetti and fruit.
Let set overnight.
Before serving, fold in Cool Whip.
Yummy!

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and let stand overnight, then drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed to boiling, then add vegetables.
Bring to boil and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Pour half the batter into a greased and floured 9 by 13 inch pan. Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins, then swirl half of the dry mixture on the batter. Add the remaining batter. Top with remaining dry mixture. Swirl top of the cake with knife to look like cinnamon buns. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk together and drizzle over cooled cake.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine together.
Pour 1/3 of melted margarine in baking dish; put remaining butter in mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut
pork
or chicken into 1-inch cubes, or form ground beef into
1-inch
balls.
Dip
in batter made of eggs, salt, pepper, flour
and	baking powder.	Cook well on all sides in hot
oil. Remove
meat
and
keep
hot.
Pour
off
all but 2 tablespoons oil.
Add green peppers, seeded and cut into small chunks,	with the chicken bouillon;
cook for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, the rest of the bouillon and the other ingredients; blend
together. Cook
until thickened; add the meat and heat through.
Serve
over hot
rice.
Garnish,
if
desired, with tomato wedges and hard-cooked eggs.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, shake all ingredients until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into a large baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at rooms temperature.
Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 or 20 minutes.
Serve while hot.
These freeze well, too.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add cream, vanilla, eggs and melted margarine.
Mix well; add nuts and coconut.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into 2 loaves; refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: hot clam spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain the juice from 1 can clams (use it for another purpose).
Melt the butter and add the drained clams, the other can of clams with juice, cracker crumbs, onion and lemon juice.
Pour into a shallow baking dish and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: honey glazed pork roast with sweet potatoes
directions: Rub roast well with salt and pepper. Cut slits in fat with a sharp knife. Roast, fat side up, in a shallow pan at 350° for 2 hours.

title: velvet salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in hot milk.
Let cool.
Dissolve yellow gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Let cool.
Combine yellow gelatin and marshmallows with cream cheese, whipped cream, yogurt and pineapple.
Pour into a large pan and refrigerate to set. Dissolve red gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Let cool.
Pour on yellow gelatin and marshmallow mixture.
Refrigerate to set.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage until tender. Drain well. In a saucepan, melt butter. Add flour, milk and salt, stirring until thickened.
Add cabbage and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a buttered casserole and top with the crumbs which have been mixed with the melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until slightly browned on top.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Saute sliced onions. Remove from pan and brown the hamburg. Return onions to pan and add bean sprouts and mushroom soup.

title: hot chile-beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a chafing dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: ham brunch casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer bread, ham and cheese ending with bread.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour slowly over the bread and ham and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Just before baking, pour over 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: hot dogs with cheesy corn topping
directions: In small bowl, combine corn, cheese, mayonnaise and green onions; mix well.
Place wieners in buns; spoon topping over wiener. Wrap each bun in heavy-duty foil.
Grill 4 to 6 minutes on medium heat or 10 to 15 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Line your dish with ice cream sandwiches.
Spread Cool Whip on that layer.
Make another layer of sandwiches and spread more Cool Whip.
You can put nuts, cherries, Hershey's sprinkles, etc. on them for decorations.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Cut in squares.

title: c&d salsa (hot sauce)
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients and blend on chop speed. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: dutch oven chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in Dutch oven until crisp-tender.
Arrange chicken in layer over vegetables; add spaghetti in a layer.
Combine soup, broth, lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over spaghetti, making certain all of spaghetti is moistened.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top.
Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Makes 4 generous servings.
Can be frozen or reheated.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.

title: sweet 'n sour kielbasa
directions: Melt butter or margarine and saute onion.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add ketchup and remaining ingredients.
Heat for 10 to 15 minutes (boil and simmer).
Pour into crock-pot (or container) with sliced kielbasa.
Use own judgement as to how much kielbasa you want in it.
Sauce is quite abundant when hot.
Serve with party-picks.
(Can be made up to two days ahead and kept in airtight container in refrigerator.
Reheat when ready to serve.)

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Saute onion and butter together. Mix all except mushrooms and onions. Simmer until cheese is melted. Add mushrooms and almonds. Serve heated. (Chafing dish item.)
